<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mozambican Party Leader Pays Tribute to Deng </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 24 (Xinhua) -- General Secretary of the
Mozambique Liberation Front Party Manuel Tome went to the Chinese
Embassy in Maputo to mourn the death of Chinese leader Deng
Xiaoping on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Tome said that it was with great sadness that he and his party
members had learned of Deng's.
</P>
<P>
"He was an outstanding, esteemed and beloved leader of the
Chinese people, the Communist Party of China and the People's
Republic of China. By his keen insight into both international and
domestic situation, Deng became the great architect of China's
reform, which has led the country toward modernization," Tome said.
</P>
<P>
He called Deng one of the most outstanding leaders in the
present times, adding that Deng, as a great statesman and
strategist who has devoted himself to the course of the Chinese
people, would be remembered forever. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
