<HEADLINE> Shipping Line Opens between Iranian, UAE Ports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, February 24 (Xinhua) -- A new shipping line Opened
today between Iran's southern port of Bandar-Lengeh and Dubai,
the United Arab Emirates.
</P>
<P>
Iran's official news agency IRNA reported that a new
passenger ship "Zomorrod" would ferry between the Iranian and the
UAE ports.
</P>
<P>
The liner will make a shuttle trip once a week on Sundays
from Iran and on Mondays from Dubai, it said.
</P>
<P>
The liner is capable of ferrying 234 passengers and 24 tonnes
of cargo and 10 motor-cars, it added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
