<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Carpet Export Fair Concludes in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, February 24 (Xinhua) -- China has become the world's
fourth-biggest carpet exporter after Iran, Turkey and India,
according to sources at the 23rd China Carpet Export Fair, which
closed here today.
</P>
<P>
A total of 292 carpet producers participated in the fair, the
biggest ever held in China, making deals worth a total of 140
million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Apart from traditional woolen hand-made carpets, many new types
of carpets made from such materials as paper, flax fiber and reeds
were displayed during the fair.
</P>
<P>
A carpet company in Henan Province even showed a
four-square-foot silk carpet, which took eight weavers three and a
half years to complete.
</P>
<P>
China has 383 carpet factories, which exported 12.02 million
square meters of carpets last year, earning 400 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, product quality has been greatly improved since a
chamber of commerce for the carpet industry was set up to exercise
strict management over the sector. 
</P>
</TEXT>
