<HEADLINE> S.African Communist Party Leader Mourns Deng's Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 24 (Xinhua) -- General Secretary of the
South African Communist Party Charles Nqakula sent a message of
condolence to Chinese President Jiang Zemin over Chinese leader
Deng Xiaoping's death.
</P>
<P>
He said that Deng is "a courageous Communist, who understood
that the socialist ideal was not a fixed blue-print," but
needed "adaptation to local, national conditions."
</P>
<P>
Nqakula said that Deng has laid a sturdy basis for China's
continued development, a path that will be pursued by his
successors. 
</P>
