<HEADLINE> Polish Senior Officials Mourn for Deng </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Polish senior officials today
visited the Chinese embassy here to mourn for Chinese leader Deng
Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
Presidential Office Director Danuta Waniek, Vice Director of
the Office of the Council of Ministers Andrej Macenowicz, and
Vice Foreign Minister Robert Mroziewicz handed in their joint
message of condolences on behalf of the Polish president, prime
minister and foreign minister.
</P>
<P>
They wrote in the book of condolences: "The departure of the
prominent statesman is a great loss to the People's Republic of
China, and the international community as well."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, foreign diplomats to Poland and representatives of
various Polish communities also visited the Chinese embassy and
paid homage to Deng. 
</P>
</TEXT>
