<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Moderate Party Tops Swedish Political Parties in Popularity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, February 24 (Xinhua) -- The electoral support for
the Swedish Moderate Party has amounted to 30.9 percent, making it
the most popular party in Sweden, Swedish Institute of Public
Opinion Research poll for February showed.
</P>
<P>
The party's major political rival, the ruling Social Democratic
Party (SDP), obtained 29.1 percent support.
</P>
<P>
The figures illustrate an obvious change of political trend in
the nation, an even wider gap between the two parties.
</P>
<P>
Moderate Party Secretary Gunnar Hokmark is convinced that the
recent energy agreement, reached between the ruling SDP and some
central and left parties, including the Moderate Party, was of
decisive importance to the changes.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the nuclear power station in Barseback, on
the western coast of the country, is scheduled to be closed by
July, 1998 before an autumn election.
</P>
<P>
However, Social Democratic Party Secretary Ingela Thalen seemed
to be satisfied with the party's steady supporting rate below 30
percent, saying it was caused by the firm but inevitable economic
policy of the last two years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
