<HEADLINE> Berlin Film Festival Awards List </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, February 24 (Xinhua) -- The two-week 47th Berlin Film
Festival concluded today after the awarding of the following
prizes:
</P>
<P>
Golden Bear: "The People vs. Larry Flynt" by Milos Forman
(U.S.);
</P>
<P>
Silver Bear, Special Jury Award: "He Liu" by Tsai Ming-Liang
(Taiwan, China);
</P>
<P>
Silver Bear (special): "Genealogies d'un Crime" (France) for
director Raoul Ruiz;
</P>
<P>
Silver Bear for best director: Eric Heumann for "Port Djema"
(France);
</P>
<P>
Silver Bear for best actor: Leonardo DiCaprio for "William
Shakespeare's Romeo and Juliet" by Baz Luhrmann (U.S.);
</P>
<P>
Silver Bear for best actress: Juliette Binoche for "The English
Patient" by Anthony Minghella (U.S.);
</P>
<P>
Silver Bear for outstanding individual achievement: Zbigniew
Preisner for screenplay of "The Island on Bird Street" by Soren
Kragh-Jacobsen (Denmark/Britain/Germany);
</P>
<P>
Honorable Mention for the films "Das Leben Ist Eine Baustelle"
by Wolfgang Becker (Germany) and "Get on the Bus" by Spike Lee
(U.S.);
</P>
<P>
Alfred Bauer Award: "William Shakespeare's Romeo and Juliet" by
Baz Luhrmann (U.S.);
</P>
<P>
Golden Bear for best short film: "Synaste Nytt" by Per Carleson
(Sweden);
</P>
<P>
Silver Bear for best short film: "Late at Night" by Stefanie
Jordan, Stefanie Saghri and Claudia Zoller (Germany);
</P>
<P>
Ecumenical Jury Award: "Leneged Enayim Maaraviot" by Joseph
Pitchhadze (Israel) and "Nobody's Business" by Alan Berliner
(U.S.);
</P>
<P>
Fipresci Preis Award of the International Film Critics
Association: "He Liu" by Tsai Ming-Liang (Taiwan, China) and
"Nobody's Business" by Alan Berliner (U.S.);
</P>
<P>
Blue Angel Award from the European Film and Television Academy
to director Montxo Armendariz for "Secretos Del Corazon" (Spain);
</P>
<P>
UNICEF Chilren's Film Award: "Kan Du Vissla, Johanna?" by Rumle
Hammerich (Sweden);
</P>
<P>
German Art Cinema Award: "Get on the Bus" by Spike Lee
(U.S.); and
</P>
<P>
Gay and Lesbian Teddy Bear Award: "All Over Me" by Alex Sichel
(U.S.). 
</P>
