<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-24 17:37 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Netanyahu to Decide On Building Jewish </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Israeli Prime Minister
Binyamin Netanyahu met Jerusalem Mayor Ehud Olmert, and promised
that a decision will be made in two days on the construction of
Har Homa neighborhood in Jerusalem, Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
Olmert told Israel Radio that he and the premier also
agreed on the building of some 3,500 housing units in ten
Arab neighborhoods in the eastern side of Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Olmert said that Netanyahu told him that he would submit
these proposals to the cabinet Wednesday for approval, adding
he believed that the construction would start in "a matter
of weeks."
</P>
<P>
On Sunday, Netanyahu, during his visit to Jordan, informed
Jordan's King Hussein that Israel plans to "simultaneously
announce this week" the construction of an estimated 2,600
Jewish housing units on Har Homa and an "approximately equal"
number of Arab units in the Jerusalem area.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Palestinians officials continued to express their
opposition to the building of the Har Homa neighborhood, even
if it was linked to the building of Arab neighborhoods in
east Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
They warned that there would be Palestinian resistance to the
construction of the Jewish neighborhood in Jerusalem, which, they
said, would lead a situation that would threaten the peace
process. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
