<HEADLINE> Container Truck Explosion Injures Three in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 24 (Xinhua) -- A container truck exploded
here today, causing slight injuries to three people, police said.
</P>
<P>
At about 5:40 PM, the truck carrying 160 motorcycles reportedly
caught fire and exploded on Lung Cheung Road, Kowloon. The
36-year-old driver immediately got out of his vehicle and was
unhurt.
</P>
<P>
Some 20 firemen rushed to the spot and the fire was put out
soon after.
</P>
<P>
However, the driver of a private car immediately behind the
truck felt unwell after stopping his car due to the explosion.
</P>
<P>
A medium goods vehicle on the opposite carriageway was also hit
by exploded objects and overturned. The driver was not hurt but
his male passenger was injured by broken glasses.
</P>
<P>
A two-year-old girl on the 7th floor of a building nearby was
hit by falling objects from a cupboard, possibly due to air
pressure generated by the explosion.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the explosion is not immediately unknown.
</P>
</TEXT>
