<HEADLINE> Algerian Security Forces Kill 83 Extremists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Algeria's security forces have
killed 83 in a vast offensive against Islamic extremists over the
past few days, local media quoted security sources as saying today.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that 60 were killed in Chrea and Medea,
respectively 60 and 90 kilometers south Algiers, and at least five
"back-up bases" of the extremist group, Armed Islamic Group (GIA),
were destroyed.
</P>
<P>
GIA, the most radical of the groups, has intensified terrorist
activities, including bombing attacks in cities and villages,
since the beginning of the Muslim fasting month of Ramadan on
January 10, during which more than 400 people were killed,
</P>
<P>
After the bloody month of Ramadan, Algerian President Liamine
Zeroual vowed to "exterminate" the groups.
</P>
<P>
According to the United States State Department estimates, the
Moslem extremists have claimed at least 60,000 lives in the past
five years in the North African country. 
</P>
