<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Good Sino-US Relations Help World Peace: Li Peng </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 24 (Xinhua) -- In a meeting with US Secretary
of State Madeleine Albright tonight, Premier Li Peng said that
increasing cooperation and the establishment of good relations
between China and the US, as two major countries, will be
significant for safeguarding world peace and promoting common
development.
</P>
<P>
Li also noted that maintaining and enhancing high-level
exchanges of visits between the two countries will also be helpful
for increasing mutual trust and understanding.
</P>
<P>
"China is willing to do anything that will benefit world peace,
security and development," Li said, adding that China observes
principles, shoulders its responsibilities and keeps its promises
in international affairs.
</P>
<P>
"We welcome Vice-President Al Gore's forthcoming visit to China
in March," Li said, adding, "I am looking forward to discussing
with him the environmental and energy cooperation and sustained
development, in order to explore new ways of expanding
mutually-beneficial cooperation in these areas, and to open up
even broader prospects for bilateral economic and trade
cooperation."
</P>
<P>
Because the two countries have different histories, traditions
and social systems, and their economies are developing on
different levels, the Chinese premier noted, it is easy to
understand that there exist disputes on some questions between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
But this should not hinder the development of Sino-US
relations, Li said, adding that the two sides should engage in
constructive dialogue in the spirit of seeking common ground while
reserving differences, since the world is diversified.
</P>
<P>
"Dialogue, instead of confrontation, is beneficial to both
sides," Li emphasized.  
</P>
</TEXT>
