<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Education Workers Commemorate Deng </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 24 (Xinhua) -- More than 100
representatives from the local educational sector gathered here
today to commemorate Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping who passed away
last Wednesday at the age of 93.
</P>
<P>
Yeung Yiu-chung, chairman of the Federation of Education
Workers, praised Deng as one of the greatest figures in today's
world.
</P>
<P>
Under his leadership, the Chinese people embarked on the road
of reform and opening-up and modern construction, and have made
great achievements featured by a growing comprehensive national
strength, an enhanced international status and improved living
standards of the people, said Yeung, who is also headmaster of
Heung To Middle School.
</P>
<P>
A teacher from Mu Kuang English School voiced his regret that
Deng, whose initiative of "one country, two systems" led to a
successful settlement of the Hong Kong issue, could not witness
the moment when Hong Kong will return to her motherland in the
middle of this year.
</P>
<P>
Many speakers agreed that the best way to commemorate Deng is
to make every effort toward Hong Kong's smooth transition and its
long-term prosperity and stability, so as to live up to Deng's
expectations.
</P>
<P>
"We should teach the younger generation to love their country
and the Chinese nation, and to study and work hard with a
perspective of a better Hong Kong," Professor Chan from the
Chinese University of Hong Kong told the gathering.
</P>
<P>
Various mourning activities have been held in Hong Kong's
schools in the past few days.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of students and teachers went to the mourning hall at
the Xinhua News Agency Hong Kong Branch here to pay their homage
to Deng Xiaoping. 
</P>
</TEXT>
