<HEADLINE> Ex-Minister to Chair Swedish Nazi Gold Commission </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Rolf Wirten, Sweden's Labor
Minister in early 1980s and a former county governor, has been
appointed chairman of an investigation commission, which will deal
with Swedish purchases of gold from Nazi during the Second World
War.
</P>
<P>
These gold could have been stolen from the Jewish people by
Germany's Nazi government.
</P>
<P>
Ragnar Sohlman, a possible nominee, missed the appointment
because of concerns of his qualification as the son of Rolf
Sohlman, the Swedish Foreign Minister during the war.
</P>
<P>
The commission will also review bank accounts opened by
persecuted European Jews before the war started.
</P>
<P>
Some reports said that these dormant accounts now contain
deposits of as many as 59 million Swedish kroner (about 7.67
million U.S. dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
