<DOCNO> XIE19970225.0053 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Roundup: HK People Continue To Mourn for Deng Xiaoping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 25 (Xinhua) -- At 10:00 am today, dozens of
ships cruising in Victoria Harbor of Hong Kong simultaneously
sounded their sirens for one minute in tribute to the late Chinese
leader Deng Xiaoping, who passed away last Wednesday at the age
of 93.
</P>
<P>
When the memorial meeting attended by 10,000 people in Beijing
began at 10:00 a.m., Hong Kong residents mourned in various forms
for Deng Xiaoping, whose concept of "one country, two systems" has
made it possible that Hong Kong will continue to prosper after its
return to the motherland in the middle of this year.
</P>
<P>
In memory of Deng, all public transport means made their own
arrangements today: on the streets of Hong Kong all the 800 buses
run by the China Motor Bus were decorated with white flowers and
black ribbons; funeral music resounded for 10 minutes in all 38
underground railway stations; trains running between Kowloon and
Canton blew their horns; and the Peak Tram suspended its services
for one minute.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, many schools on the Hong Kong Island and Kowloon,
including Pui Kiu Middle School, Hon Wah Middle School, Heung To
Middle School, Fukien Middle School and Mong Kok Workers' Children
School, held memorial meetings this morning to mourn the death of
Deng.
</P>
<P>
In Heung To Middle School, more than 1,000 students and
teachers gathered this morning in a memorial meeting held at the
school's meeting hall, which was solemnly decorated with a large
portrait of Deng on the rostrum.
</P>
<P>
At 9:30 a.m. when the memorial meeting began, all the people
present stood in silent tribute for three minutes.
</P>
<P>
Headmaster of the school Yeung Yiu-chung said in his speech
that Deng devised the great concept of "one country, two systems,"
which is in accordance with the Hong Kong people's interests and
has won the Hong Kong people's support. The Hong Kong people will
always cherish the memory of him.
</P>
<P>
"We deeply regret that Deng Xiaoping could not fulfill his wish
to set foot on the land of Hong Kong at the returning day. We
believe that the best way to commemorate the great man is to
realize Hong Kong's smooth transition, ensure its stability and
prosperity," he said.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on behalf of all students in the school, a student
representative said: "Beloved Deng Xiaoping devoted his whole life
to the motherland and the nation. Whenever we see our motherland
is progressing ever stronger and people's living standards
constantly improving, we will recall his great deeds."
</P>
<P>
He called on his school mates to study diligently so as to make
greater contributions to the motherland, pledging to do their best
to live up to Deng's expectations.
</P>
<P>
While watching live TV broadcast of the memorial meeting in
Beijing at 10:00 a.m., many students and teachers here shed tears.
</P>
<P>
At the Workers' Club of the Hong Kong Federation of Trade
Unions, more than 350 workers' representatives stood for a whole
hour to watch live TV broadcast of the memorial meeting in
Beijing, while tens of thousands of members of the Federation also
watched the broadcast at its branch offices.
</P>
<P>
"He has done so much for the Chinese people, so much for Hong
Kong, we should pay our most sincere respects to him," a worker
said.
</P>
<P>
Many other social groups and organizations also held memorial
meetings this morning. These include Hong Kong Chinese Chamber of
Commerce, New Territory Federation of Societies, Bank of China
Group, Hong Kong China Importers' and Exporters' Association and
Democratic Alliance for Betterment of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Joint Publishing (HK) Co. Ltd issued portraits and badges of
Deng today, attracting thousands of people.
</P>
<P>
Over the past few days more than 45,000 people went to the
mourning hall at the office building of the Xinhua News Agency
Hong Kong Branch to offer their condolences, with more than 1,200
wreaths sent there in memory of Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Director of the Xinhua News Agency Hong Kong Branch Zhang
Junsheng said that the mourning activities in Hong Kong fully
showed the Hong Kong people's understanding of Deng's great deeds
and contributions and their respects for him. 
</P>
</TEXT>
