<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Beats Malaysia in Dunhill Cup Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, February 25 (Xinhua) -- China defeated hosts
Malaysia 2-0 in its final Group A match at the Dunhill Cup soccer
tournament here Tuesday evening.
</P>
<P>
After the first half ended at 0-all, the Chinese eleven
intensified their attack and had two goals through Su Maozhen and
Sui Dongliang at the 60th and 74th minute respectively.
</P>
<P>
In another match from the group this evening, Finland edged
Singapore 1-0.
</P>
<P>
After the group round robins, China had three wins from as many
matches and Malaysia one win, one draw and one defeat. The two
teams finished 1-2 in the group standings and advanced into the
semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
Wednesday will feature two final matches from Group B, with
Bosnia-Herzegovina taking Indonesia and Zimbabwe facing Vietnam.
</P>
</TEXT>
