<HEADLINE> Bilardo Leaves Sevilla after Four Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, February 25 (Xinhua) -- Carlos Bilardo, who led
Argentina for a World Cup title, has resigned as boss of
struggling Sevilla less than a month after he took over at the
Spanish first division club.
</P>
<P>
"From the start nothing went well," said Bilardo, who guided
Argentina to success in the 1986 World Cup but had lost three of
his four games in charge in his second spell in the southern
Spanish city.
</P>
<P>
He had returned to take over from Jose Antonio Camacho, but
found himself unable to cope with the underlying instability of a
club wracked by boardroom conflict and financial problems.
</P>
<P>
Bilardo will be replaced on a temporary basis by second-team
coach Julian Rubio. 
