<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Ministry to Take Legal Measures to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, February 25 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Ministry of
Trade and Industry has announced that most of the 20,000 business
organizations engaged in foreign trade are operating without
having their licenses renewed and the ministry is bracing to take
legal measures that will include revoking licenses.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ethiopian News Agency today, the announcement
was made by Kasahun Ayele, Minister of Trade and Industry at the
Ethiopian parliament, the house of people's representatives on
the draft proclamation on commercial registration and business
licensing Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Minister said close to 12,000 business centers and service
rendering institutions have failed to comply with the regulation
that states the renewal of licenses within six months after the
expiry of the budget year in which the license has been issued or
renewed.
</P>
<P>
He said the government has extended the date for the
cancellation of licenses up until next month, adding that most of
the organizations have failed to abide by the law despite
repeated announcements on the media.
</P>
<P>
However, the minister said any individual who could not get
access to equitable services is allowed to forward grievances to
the minister and vice-minister. enditem

