<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, Portugal Encourage More Exchanges Between Congresses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 25 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, chairman of China's
National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, met here
today with visiting Portuguese President Jorge Sampaio.
</P>
<P>
Sampaio arrived in Beijing on February 23 for a state visit to
China. During his meetings with Chinese leaders he several times
expressed his condolences over the death of Chinese leader Deng
Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
Expressing his appreciation, Qiao said, "A solemn memorial
meeting for Comrade Deng Xiaoping was held at the Great Hall of
the People this morning. The Chinese people are determined to turn
grief into strength and continue to unswervingly follow the road
of building socialism with Chinese characteristics, which was
initiated by Comrade Deng."
</P>
<P>
Qiao welcomed Sampaio's state visit to China. He said that
since the establishment of Sino-Portuguese diplomatic relations in
1979, the two countries have developed friendly cooperative
relations in various fields.
</P>
<P>
There has been good cooperation between the NPC and the
Parliament of Portugal, Qiao said, adding that the visit by the
president of the Portuguese Parliament to China in 1988 and the
visit by NPC leaders to Portugal have played an active role in
enhancing the development of bilateral relations of cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He said that the NPC is willing to keep and strengthen its
friendly cooperation with the Parliament of Portugal in an effort
to further develop bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Sampaio noted that he was visiting China at an important
moment. He said he hoped that the current visit would help make
Portuguese-Chinese ties more secure.
</P>
<P>
He said, "The Parliament of Portugal maintains a good
relationship with the NPC." According to Sampaio, his entourage
includes senior Portuguese parliamentarians, who appreciate the
NPC's efforts to improve China's legal system, are very interested
in obtaining more knowledge about the NPC and expect more
exchanges between the two congresses.
</P>
<P>
As for the issue of Macao, Qiao said that, based on the idea of
"one country, two systems," the Sino-Portuguese joint declaration
on the Macao issue was signed in 1987, which sets a good example
for the whole world for the settlement of problems left over from
history through peaceful negotiation.
</P>
<P>
The NPC passed the basic law of the Macao Special
Administrative Region (MSAR) in 1993, defining China's basic
policy of carrying out the policy of "one country, two systems" in
Macao in the form of legal provisions.
</P>
<P>
After China's resumption of the exercise of its sovereignty
over Macao, the NPC will support the implementation of the policy
of "one country, two systems" in the MSAR, Qiao noted. It will
also honor its commitment in the joint declaration of implementing
the MSAR basic law and realizing a "high degree of autonomy" and
"Macao people governing Macao," he added.
</P>
<P>
Sampaio said he was glad to see that the Portuguese-Chinese
joint declaration and the MSAR basic law have high legal status in
China. He added that he has great confidence in Macao's stable
transition and a "high degree of autonomy" in Macao after its
return to its motherland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
