<HEADLINE> Seminar Seeks Ways to Help Ex-Serviceman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 25 (Xinhua) -- A seminar was held here from
February 23 to 25 to find ways of establishing social security
systems and providing better employment opportunities for
ex-servicemen.
</P>
<P>
China has an annual batch of more than 600,000 demobilized
serviceman, accounting for a large part of the country's labor
force. Of the more than four million people assigned jobs in
cities and towns by the state in 1994, 15 percent were
ex-serviceman.
</P>
<P>
With the establishment of the market-oriented socialist
economic system, the employment of ex-serviceman has met some
difficulties, and the government has been trying to tackle the
problem both theoretically and practically. 
