<HEADLINE> People's Daily Editorial Mourns Deng's Passing (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 25 (Xinhua) -- China's leading newspaper, the
People's Daily, will publish an editorial tomorrow lamenting the
passing of Comrade Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
The full text of the editorial, entitled "Recalling
Contributions, Inheriting the Legacy, and Jointly Accomplishing
the Great Cause", is as follows:
</P>
<P>
Our beloved Comrade Deng Xiaoping passed away on February 19,
1997, leaving the entire Chinese nation in a state of profound
grief. The Party, the Army, and the people of all ethnic groups
throughout China, struck by a sense of deep sorrow, have expressed
their heartfelt mourning.
</P>
<P>
Comrade Deng was an outstanding leader whose great prestige was
acknowledged by the whole Party, Army, and people of all ethnic
groups throughout China. He was a great Marxist, a great
proletarian revolutionary, a statesman, a military strategist and
a diplomat, and a long tested communist fighter, the chief
architect of China's socialist reforms, opening-up, and
modernization drive, and the founder of the theory of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
In his revolutionary career of over seven decades, Deng made an
indelible historic contribution to the liberation and happiness of
the Chinese people, to the independence and prosperity of the
Chinese nation, and to the peace and progress of the world,
leaving us with an exceedingly rich and valuable spiritual legacy.
</P>
<P>
Comrade Deng Xiaoping was a great man of the century with
outstanding exploits. His passing represents an immeasurable loss
to the Communist Party of China and to the Chinese people, and his
great name will go down in Chinese history and in world history as
well.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970225.0080 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People's Daily Editorial Mourns Deng's Passing (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The great life of Comrade Deng Xiaoping spanned the entire 20th
century as a magnificent epic, a painted scroll of splendid sweep,
and a movement of resounding music. His great achievements, his
scientific theories, his revolutionary style, and his grand
trans-century blueprint, will never be forgotten by the Communist
Party of China or the Chinese people and, will forever inspire and
encourage us to advance bravely in fulfiling the great
expectations of the Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
We will never forget Comrade Deng Xiaoping's great
achievements. In the long years of revolutionary wars, Comrade
Deng was repeatedly entrusted with important missions, and with no
fear for hardship or danger, he fought bravely and performed
immortal feats for the founding of New China. In the early years
of New China, he worked effectively for the establishment of the
socialist system and for the development of socialist
construction. During the "Cultural Revolution", he firmly upheld
truths and fought against the "Gang of Four" unswervingly.
</P>
<P>
After the Third Plenum of the 11th CPC Central Committee in
particular, Comrade Deng Xiaoping, who was more than 70 then,
added the most glorious chapter to his life. With a dauntless
revolutionary spirit, he launched the drive to rectify the chaos
of the time and bravely re-established the ideological line of
emancipating the mind and seeking truth from facts, leading the
Party and the whole nation to a historic change and opening a new
historical period of reforms, opening-up, and focusing on the
socialist modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
In the past 18 years, China's economic development has seen
achievements that have attracted worldwide attention, and its
national strength has gained marked growth, with the people's
standard of living improving significantly, the country's outlook
undergoing profound changes. In this, socialist China has shown
great vitality and vigor and, internationally its status has risen
to unprecedented heights. With the guidance of an outstanding
leader with political vision like Comrade Deng Xiaoping, our Party
and our country have left behind the disasters of the "Cultural
Revolution", avoided falling into a new period of chaos and
confusion, and successfully embarked onto a road of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics. This has been the good
fortune and pride of the Chinese Communist Party and of the
Chinese people.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
