<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People's Daily Editorial Mourns Deng's Passing (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
We shall cherish the memory of Comrade Deng's great strength of
character. He was unceasingly loyal to the Party, the nation and
the people. He said: "My life belongs to the Party, to the
country," and "I am the son of the Chinese people. I love my
motherland and my people deeply."
</P>
<P>
Precisely because of this, he showed great respect for the
people, serving them with all his heart, and always paying close
attention to their interests and aspirations. He always considered
whether something would boost the productive forces of the
socialist society, enhance the country's comprehensive national
strength, and improve people's standard of living as both the
starting point and the goal in formulating principles and policies.
</P>
<P>
Precisely because of this, he valued practice, sought truth
from facts, was good at feeling the pulse of the times and using
opportunities for development. He always tried to sum up fresh
experience, create new methods and look for new ways based on
China's reality and developments of the contemporary world.
</P>
<P>
Because of this, he was far-sighted, broad-minded, selfless,
and dauntless, unyielding, heedless of personal safety, and of
personal ups and downs. He always took the entire situation into
account, observing and tackling major issues by keeping in mind
the fundamental interests of the nation and the people.
</P>
<P>
Because of this, he had firm beliefs and a strong will, was
pragmatic, and made scientific decisions at crucial moments, which
demonstrated his extraordinary courage and insight.
</P>
<P>
Comrade Deng Xiaoping, with his lofty and distinct
revolutionary style, will forever be the model for Chinese
Communists.
</P>
</TEXT>
