<HEADLINE> S.Korean Parliament Leader Mourns Deng's Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 25 (Xinhua) -- Speaker of South Korea's
National Assembly (parliament) Kim Soo-han has sent a message of
condolences over the death of Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
In the message to his Chinese counterpart, Qiao Shi, Kim said
it was with an undescribable sense of loss that he, on behalf of
all his colleagues in the parliament, offers the deepest
condolences on Deng's death.
</P>
<P>
Kim said that Deng's "unparalleled wisdom and determination
successfully lead the Chinese people in the transition to a
socialist market economy and thus paved the way for a new era of
co-prosperity and peace not only in our region but also around the
globe, was an enduring inspiration and the object of infinite
admiration for the Korean people."
</P>
<P>
He added, "it is difficult to imagine a world without him, but
we take solace in knowing that his legacy shall live in our hearts
long into the next century."
</P>
<P>
"Our thoughts are with you and the people of China in this time
of great bereavement," the speaker said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
