<HEADLINE> People's Daily Editorial Mourns Deng's Passing (5) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
We shall forever cherish the memory of Comrade Deng Xiaoping's
great ideals. Comrade Deng was a devoted Communist. He showed
great foresight, and possessed a scientific and creative mind.
</P>
<P>
Combining his lofty ideals with the reality of the initial
stage of socialism in our country, he proposed the theory of
building socialism with Chinese characteristics, drew up a
blueprint for revitalizing the Chinese nation, and a three-step
development strategy of turning our poor country into a strong and
prosperous nation.
</P>
<P>
According to that strategy, the Chinese people will be
comfortably well-off by the end of the century, and will reach the
standard of living of certain developed nations in the middle of
the next century and be built into a prosperous, democratic,
civilized, and modernized socialist country. This has become a
common ideal for the people of the country's various ethnic groups.
</P>
<P>
Comrade Deng was adept at combining the strictness of
principles with the flexibility of tactics. He developed the idea
of "one country, two systems" as the way to complete the great
cause of national reunification. Propelled by this concept, our
country will resume sovereignty over Hong Kong on July 1 of this
year, putting an end to more than a century of national
humiliation.
</P>
<P>
During his lifetime, Comrade Deng expressed his hope to visit
Hong Kong after its return to the motherland. But now, with less
than 130 days to Hong Kong's return, Comrade Deng Xiaoping, to our
great sorrow, has passed away. Although his long-cherished wish is
not to be realized, his legacy certainly will be.
</P>
</TEXT>
