<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Students Mourn for Deng Xiaoping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 25 (Xinhua) -- More than 1,000 students and
teachers of Heung To Middle School on the Hong Kong Island
gathered together this morning in a memorial meeting to mourn over
the death of Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
The memorial meeting was held at the school's meeting hall,
which was solemnly decorated with a large portrait of Deng on the
rostrum.
</P>
<P>
At 9:00 a.m. when the memorial meeting began, all the people
present stood in silent tribute for three minutes.
</P>
<P>
Headmaster of the school Yeung Yiu-chung said in his speech
that Deng was the architect of China's reform and opening-up
policy and modernization drive. Under his leadership, China's
comprehensive national strength was reinforced and people's living
standards improved, he added.
</P>
<P>
"He is also the inventor of the great concept of 'one country
two systems,' which is in accordance with the Hong Kong people's
interests and has won the Hong Kong people's support, we Hong Kong
people will never forget him," Yeung said.
</P>
<P>
He said that there are only 126 days left before Hong Kong
returns to the motherland. The Preparatory Committee, the Chief
Executive and the Provisional Legislative Council are carrying out
various tasks for forming the Special Administrative Region
government in an orderly way.
</P>
<P>
"We regret very much that Deng Xiaoping could not fulfill his
wish to step on the land of Hong Kong at the returning day. We
believe that the best way to commemorate the great man is to
realize Hong Kong's smooth transition, ensure its stability and
prosperity," he said.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on behalf of all the students in the school, a student
representative said: "Beloved Deng Xiaoping devoted his whole life
to the motherland and the nation, whenever we see our motherland
is progressing ever stronger and people's living standards
constantly improving, we will recall his great deeds."
</P>
<P>
"Deng Xiaoping has passed away, but his spirit of 'seeking
truth from reality' and his noble personality will stay in our
heart forever," he said.
</P>
<P>
He called on his school mates to study diligently and
contribute to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
"We'll never let Deng's expectations down," he said.
</P>
<P>
At 10:00 a.m. the students and teachers watched live TV
broadcast of the 10,000-people memorial meeting in Beijing. Many
of them shed tears.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, many other schools in Hong Kong, such as Pui Kiu
Middle School and Hon Wah Middle School, also held memorial
meetings this morning for teachers and students to mourn for
Deng. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
