<HEADLINE> Bonilla Retains WBA Flyweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, February 25 (Xinhua) -- WBA flyweight champion Jose
Bonilla of Venezuela beat Japan's Hiroki Ioka with a technical
knockout in the seventh round to win his first title defence in
Osaka, Japan on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The knockout time came two minutes 49 seconds into the round
when American referee Rafael Ramos stopped the fight to declare
the 29-year-old champion as the winner of the World Boxing
Association bout.
</P>
<P>
Bonilla wrested the title from Saen Sor-Ploenchit of Thailand
in November last year.
</P>
<P>
Bonilla stretched his record to 22 wins, including 11 KOs,
against three defeats. 
</P>
