<HEADLINE> HK Begins To Enjoy Fruit From New Airport Core Program: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 25 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong is beginning to
enjoy "the fruits of a grand vision" with the progressive
completion of the Airport Core Program (ACP), a leading official
of the Airport Consultative Committee said here today.
</P>
<P>
Officiating the opening ceremony of the Sai Ying Pun section of
Route 7, Hu Fa-kuang said the road is one of the early harvests.
</P>
<P>
"The opening tomorrow (of the road) will bring about
substantial improvement to the traffic along our western
waterfront and, finally, usher in the traffic to our third tunnel,
our first dual three-lane Western Harbor Crossing," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said the opening here today of the Sai Ying Pun section of
Route 7 to traffic would be welcome by the general public and he
looked forward to the public opening of the Western Harbor
Crossing in April.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening ceremony, Director of Highways
K. S. Leung said the section is another essential part of the ACP
transport corridor which links Hong Kong via the Western Harbor
Crossing to the new airport at Chek Lap Kok.
</P>
<P>
Constructed as part of the Western Harbor Crossing, the road
section also provides an additional, high-capacity road link to
the northwestern part of the Hong Kong Island, thus improving the
traffic in the area. 
</P>
