<HEADLINE> HK To Stage International Jewelry Show in March </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 25 (Xinhua) -- More than 600 local and
overseas exhibitors will converge here next month to display their
finest jewelry products at the 14th Hong Kong International
Jewelry Show.
</P>
<P>
Exhibits will include a variety of precious jewelry, jewelry
watches, precious and semi-precious stones, carvings and
ornaments, spare parts, tools and equipment for jewelry products.
</P>
<P>
More than 10,000 buyers and visitors from around the world are
expected to visit the show, which is to be held from March 12 to
15 at the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center.
</P>
<P>
As one of the most important showcases for the jewelry
industry, the show will further strengthen Hong Kong's position as
a regional trading and sourcing center for jewelry products, the
co-organizer of the event, the Hong Kong Trade Development
Council, said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Other organizers are the Hong Kong Jewelers' &AMP; Goldsmiths'
Association, the Hong Kong Jade &AMP; Stone Manufacturers Association,
the Hong Kong Jewelry Manufacturers' Association and the Diamond
Importers Association.
</P>
<P>
Figures show that Hong Kong is one of the world's largest
exporters of jewelry. In the first 11 months of 1996, Hong Kong's
total exports of jewelry reached nearly 10 billion HK dollars (1.3
billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The United States remains the territory's largest market,
absorbing more than one-third of Hong Kong's total exports and it
is followed by Japan, Germany, Singapore and France. 
</P>
</TEXT>
