<HEADLINE> Sixth Clubs Enter Intertoo Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, February 25 (Xinhua) -- European soccer governing body
UEFA said on Tuesday 60 clubs from 33 countries would compete in
this year's Intertoto Cup but soccer associations from England,
Italy and Spain had declined to take part.
</P>
<P>
France, Germany and Belgium top the list of entries with four
teams each while Russia, Turkey, Austria, Yugoslavia and Denmark
will each receive three berths.
</P>
<P>
Despite the lure of places in the first round of the UEFA Cup
for the top three finishers, nine countries -- England, Italy,
Spain, Portugal, Scotland, Luxembourg, Ukraine, Albania and
Azerbaijan -- had decided not to participate in the competition,
which is scheduled for June and July.
</P>
<P>
Last season French side Bordeaux went from the Intertoto to the
UEFA Cup final. During the same season premier league Tottenham
Hotspur were heavily fined by UEFA for fielding what it described
as under-strength teams in the Intertoto Cup. 
</P>
