<HEADLINE> Daehlie Wins in Nordic Skiing Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, February 25 (Xinhua) -- Bjorn Daehlie of Norway
claimed his second gold medal at the Nordic skiing world
championships when he won the 15km freestyle pursuit in 36 minutes
30 seconds in Trondheim, Norway on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
He finished 50 seconds ahead of Finland's Mika Myllyla, who
beat Russia's Alexi Prokurorov on the line.
</P>
<P>
Myllyla started five seconds behind Prokurorov based on his
result in Monday's 10km which Daehlie won.
</P>
<P>
Daehlie was also second to Prokurorov in last Friday's 30km
race. 
