<HEADLINE> Share Prices Go Down Sharply on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, February 25 (Xinhua) -- Share prices declined
sharply for the second day running on the Singapore market as the
benchmark Straits Times Industrials Index lost 32.02 points to
close at 2201.97 points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume stood at 502.02 million units, worth
958.74 million Singapore dollars (about 675.17 million U.S.
dollars). Advances led declines 183 to 179 while 242 other
counters remained steady.
</P>
<P>
Promet was the most actively traded stock as it registered a
turnover of 32.66 million units. It was followed by Insas Bhd
which had 26.13 million of its shares traded. Pacific Andes was
next with 17.87 million of its shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign recovered its loss
on Monday and led the gainers of the day as it rose by 1 Singapore
dollar to finish at 27.4 Singapore dollars. Local property giant
City Development increased by 50 cents to close at 14.4 Singapore
dollars while Westmont Land was 46 cents higher at 3.36 Singapore
dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, the United Overseas Bank (UOB) Foreign was the
biggest loser as it declined by 60 cents to end at 16 Singapore
dollars. Local drinks and food maker YHS lost 45 cents to close at
5 Singapore dollars while car dealer Cycle &AMP; Carriage (C&AMP;C)
finished 40 cents lower at 15.8 Singapore dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
