<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Swiss Bobsleigh Teams Stripped of Medals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, February 25 (Xinhua) -- World bobsleigh governing body
on Tuesday confirmed the disqualification of three Swiss teams
that won world championship medals using illegal axles on their
machines.
</P>
<P>
The International Bobsleigh Federation (FIBT) carried out
technical checks at the end of the four-men race at the world
championships on February 2 at St Moritz, Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
They disqualified the Switzerland 1, 2 and 3 teams piloted by
Marcel Rohner, Reto Goetschi and Christian Reich -- as they found
breaches of international rules on the front axles of all three
sleds and the rear axle of Rohner's sled.
</P>
<P>
The Swiss federation appealed against the first such
disqualification at the world championships in the 73 years of
competition. This meant medals were not immediately awarded to
eventual winners and runners-up, Germany 1 and 2, piloted by
veteran Wolfgang Poppe and Dirk Wiese, and bronze medallists the
United States, driven by Brian Shimer.
</P>
<P>
The FIBT asked its material commission to review the
information and confirm or reconsider its report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
