<HEADLINE> ASEAN Broadcasters Confederation Proposed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, February 25 (Xinhua) -- The Malaysian National
Broadcasters Association (MNBA) today proposed the formation of an
ASEAN Broadcasters Confederation (ABC).
</P>
<P>
The proposal was made by MNBA President Ismail Mustapa in his
paper presented at the five-day ASEAN Broadcasters Conference
which opened in Langkawi, a tourist resort island in the north of
Malaysia, according to the Malaysian news agency Bernama.
</P>
<P>
Ismail said the spirit of the Association of Southeast Asian
Nations (ASEAN) has permeated to all strata of society but is
somewhat subdued among broadcasters.
</P>
<P>
"The police have got their cooperative effort going very
strongly now, the same thing with the customs, the travel and tour
operators, the doctors, the engineers, journalists... What about
us, the broadcasters? We are supposed to be the master of the
airwaves. Are we devoid of the ASEAN spirit of cooperation?" he
was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The conference, being attended by about 100 broadcasters from
the seven ASEAN countries -- Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia,
Singapore, the Philippines, Thailand and Vietnam -- and Myanmar,
was likely to discuss important points such as leadership and
articles of instruments for the formation of the ABC, Ismail said.
</P>
<P>
The conference would also discuss subjects related to
collaboration in training, exchange of programs and personnel,
research and development and censorship.  
</P>
</TEXT>
