<HEADLINE> Fund to Former Zambian President Slashed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, February 25 (Xinhua) -- The Zambian government has
slashed fund to the office of former President Kenneth Kaunda by
219.1 million Kwacha (about 168,500 US Dollars), according to
today's Financial Mail.
</P>
<P>
The government fund has been reduced to 128.4 million Kwacha
this year from annual 347.5 million Kwacha in the past years.
</P>
<P>
Kaunda's aide dismissed the reduction as malicious.
</P>
<P>
"Capital expenditure for the office includes three official
cars, an official house and an office. The former president has
received nothing amid claims that he is looked after well,"
Kaunda's Special Assistant Muhabi Lungu was quoted as saying by
the local newspaper.
</P>
<P>
An official source said the cut was due to poor economic
performance over the years and current donor squeeze. 
