<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Solemn Memorial Meeting Held for Deng Xiaoping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 25 (Xinhua) -- A solemn memorial meeting
attended by 10,000 people was held Tuesday morning at the Great
Hall of the People for Comrade Deng Xiaoping, who passed away last
Wednesday at the age of 93.
</P>
<P>
Among those invited to the service, which was telecast live for
both domestic and overseas audiences, were members of the Funeral
Committee or the representatives for some members who were away
from Beijing, representatives of the Party and government
institutions, army headquarters, people's organizations, and people
from all walks of life in the Chinese capital, Deng's friends and
representatives from his hometown.
</P>
<P>
Throughout the 70-minute service, the main hall of the Great
Hall of the People had an air of solemnity about it. Hanging above
the rostrum was a large banner bearing the words "Memorial Meeting
of Comrade Deng Xiaoping." Two streamers hang from the balconies of
the second and third floors of the main hall.
</P>
<P>
One was inscribed with the words "Eternal Glory to Comrade Deng
Xiaoping who enjoys the love and esteem of the people of the whole
Party, the whole army and people of all ethnic groups throughout
the country." The other exhorted people to "Carry forward the
behest of Comrade Deng Xiaoping and advance the great cause of
building socialism with Chinese characteristics under the
leadership of the CPC Central Committee with Comrade Jiang Zemin
at the core."
</P>
<P>
The rostrum of the main hall had a silver-grey backdrop, with a
large color portrait of Deng, 5.2 meters high and 4 meters wide,
hanging in the middle. Deng's casket was covered with the flag of
the Communist Party of China and was placed amidst bouquets of
flowers and sprigs of evergreen and cypress.
</P>
<P>
A floral arrangement presented by relatives of Comrade Deng was
placed in front of the casket. On both sides of the rostrum were
wreaths sent by the CPC Central Committee, the Standing Committee
of the National People's Congress (NPC), the National Committee of
the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC),
the Central Military Commission, the Revolutionary Committee of
the Chinese Kuomintang, China Democratic League, China Democratic
National Construction Association, China Association for Promoting
Democracy, Chinese Peasants and Workers Democratic Party, the
China Zhi Gong Party, Jiu San (September 3 Society, and Taiwan
Democratic Self-Government League.
</P>
<P>
There were also wreaths on both sides of the rostrum presented
by China's party and government leaders, people without any party
affiliation, the All-China Federation of Industry and Commerce,
various people's organizations, and people from various walks of
life in the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
At 9:45, the curtain in the auditorium of the Great Hall of the
People was raised and all present at the service plunged into solemn
silence. Comrade Deng's family members were led to the front of the
hall. Party and state leaders Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, Qiao Shi, Li
Ruihuan, Zhu Rongji, Liu Huaqing, Hu Jintao and Rong Yiren,
wearing the traditional white paper flowers and black armbands of
mourning, stood in the front row.
</P>
<P>
At 10:00, Premier Li Peng, who is a member of the Standing
Committee of the CPC Central Committee Politburo, proclaimed the
opening of the memorial meeting for Comrade Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
Then, whistles on trains, ships, warships, and in factories
across China sounded for three minutes, in tribute to the
venerable leader.
</P>
<P>
After the playing of the national anthem, President Jiang
Zemin, who is general secretary of the CPC Central Committee,
spoke to the assembled gathering.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who is also chairman of the Central Military Commission,
hailed Comrade Deng Xiaoping as "an outstanding leader whose
immense prestige was recognized by the Party, the army, and the
people of all ethnic groups throughout China."
</P>
<P>
He said that Deng was a great Marxist, a great proletarian
revolutionary, statesman, military strategist, and diplomat, and a
long-tested Communist fighter, the chief architect of China's
socialist reforms, opening-up, and modernization drive, and the
founder of the theory of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said under the staunch leadership of the Party Central
Committee, the whole Party, the whole army, and the people of
various ethnic groups across China will certainly push forward the
great cause of building socialism with Chinese characteristics
pioneered by Comrade Deng Xiaoping and turn the country into a
socialist and modernized country which is powerful, prosperous,
democratic, and with a high degree of socialist ethics and
cultural development.
</P>
<P>
The CPC Central Committee called on the whole Party, the whole
army, and the people of all ethnic groups across the country to
turn grief into strength, carry on the behest of Comrade Deng
Xiaoping, and express the mourning by working harder and doing
well in all aspects of practical work, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
After Jiang's speech, all present bowed three times to Comrade
Deng to express their feelings of reverence and to honor the
memory of his more than 70-year-long revolutionary career, his
leadership and victory in China's new democratic revolution, the
founding of New China, and the establishment, consolidation and
development of the Chinese cause of socialism.
</P>
<P>
The conclusion of the memorial meeting was accompanied by the
Internationale. Jiang and the other Chinese leaders shook hands
with Zhuo Lin, Deng's widow, and with his sons and daughters and
expressed their condolences. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
