<DOCNO> XIE19970225.0139 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zhejiang to Invest Heavily in Posts and Telecom Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 25 (Xinhua) -- East China's Zhejiang Province
will inject about eight billion yuan (about 963.9 million US
dollars) into the fixed assets of its booming posts and
telecommunications business this year.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai-based Business News said that the province will
focus attention on the building of telecom networks and improving
the switching capacity of long-distance telephony service.
</P>
<P>
Its telephone switching capacity will be increased by one
million lines this year, and 20,000 channels and 253 base stations
will be added to the mobile telecom system.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the coverage of GSM (global service for mobile
communication) service will extend to most townships, and about
4,000 access lines will be added to the province's fledgling data
telecom system, which is based on several public information
service networks and Internet nodes, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
According to the plan of the Zhejiang Posts and
Telecommunications Administration, a satellite ground station will
be launched in the province's capital Hangzhou, and all the
townships will be connected to each other by optical cables.
</P>
</TEXT>
