<HEADLINE> Political Solution Key to Zaire War: S. African </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, February 25 (Xinhua) -- Visiting South African
Chief of Defense Forces General George Meirring has said a
political and not military solution is the key to end Africa's
latest war in Zaire.
</P>
<P>
He said this here on Monday in a joint interview with
reporters after he arrived for a four-day official visit to
Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
Meirring added that the war in Zaire, pitting the country's
ill-disciplined army against Rwandan-backed rebels of
the Alliance of Democratic Forces for the Liberation of
Congo-Zaire, is more a political than military upheaval.
</P>
<P>
He noted, "I think the problems will not be solved militarily.
They must be solved politically and diplomatically inside Zaire".
</P>
<P>
Meirring, South Africa's first post-apartheid Chief of Defense
Forces, is visiting Tanzania to discuss bilateral defense
co-operation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
