<HEADLINE> Zambia to Turn Livingstone Into Duty-free Zone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, February 25 (Xinhua) -- Zambia will soon turn
Livingstone in the south of the country into a duty-free zone,
"The Post" reported today.
</P>
<P>
Announcing the decision in Livingstone on Monday, Deputy
Commerce Minister Ackim Nkole said the move will reduce the high
unemployment rate of 85 percent in the area, which is the most famous
tourism spot in the southern African country.
</P>
<P>
During his tour in Livingstone, Nkole
also said Zambia and Zimbabwe will soon sign a free trade
agreement in order to level the economic playing ground between
the two neighbors.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the value-added taxes will be removed in
all duty-free zones. 
</P>
