<HEADLINE> Two Provincial Firms to Sell Shares to Fund Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 25 (Xinhua) -- Two inland firms are poised to
use the securities market to raise funds to fuel future growth by
issuing more than 61.29 million yuan (7.38 million US dollars) A
shares starting today.
</P>
<P>
Today's China Daily said that the two companies, Xianyang
Pianzhuan Ltd. in Shaanxi Province and Hunan's Zhenghong Fodder
Ltd., will also apply to list their shares on Shenzhen Securities
Exchange "as soon as possible," according to their prospectuses.
</P>
<P>
Pianzhuan is planning to collect 63.2 million yuan through
issuing 11.29 million shares priced at 5.96 yuan (0.7 US
dollars)each.
</P>
<P>
The fund will be poured into three production expansion
projects which will involve a total investment of 67.88 million
yuan (8.1 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
When completed, the company will have an annual production
capacity of 4.1 million yokes to used in 20-. 21-, 25- and 29-inch
color television kinescopes.
</P>
<P>
So far, there is still no factory in China producing yokes used
for 29-inch color televisions. Domestic television manufacturers
have to rely on imports.
</P>
<P>
Zhenghong Fodder is expected to float 50 million shares to
raise 341 million yuan (41 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The company will use part of the collected funds to expand the
production capacity of 10 subsidiaries co-funded with domestic
partners.
</P>
<P>
The company's products are sold in 13 provinces and autonomous
regions, and account for over 30 percent of the Hunan market.
</P>
</TEXT>
