<HEADLINE> Uganda to Create More Districts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, February 25 (Xinhua) -- Uganda is to create six more
districts in addition to the existing 39, reported the local
daily "The New Vision" today.
</P>
<P>
A reliable source in the Ministry of Local Government was
quoted as saying that the new districts yet to be approved by the
cabinet and parliament will include Sembabule, Busia, Kalakwi,
Nakasongola, Koboko and Bukholi.
</P>
<P>
The six districts are among the 10 regions that applied to be
upgraded to full district status.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with the Uganda New Constitution (1995), the
national parliament has the right to alter the boundaries
between districts and create new districts.
</P>
<P>
Under the central government, Uganda has 39 districts at
present. 
</P>
</TEXT>
