<HEADLINE> Air Tanzania to Extend Route to Jeddah </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, February 25 (Xinhua) -- Air Tanzania
Corporation (ATC) is expected to extend its route from the
Tanzanian capital to Jeddah, Saudi Arabia, in April.
</P>
<P>
The local paper "Guardian" today quoted ATC Acting Managing
Director Dominic Rwehumbiza as saying that the new route has been
established following completion of rehabilitation of the ATC's
two Boeing 737 planes.
</P>
<P>
The two planes were overhauled in Ireland and France, he said,
noting that arrangements are underway with Middle East airlines
to enable them to take ATC passengers to other destinations in
the world.
</P>
<P>
At the moment, the ATC operates Dar-Dubai direct flight and
weekly Dar-Johannesburg flight under a joint venture agreement
with Air Malawi, using Malawi planes.
</P>
<P>
Other ATC destinations from Dar es Salaam include Kigali in
Rwanda, Nairobi and Mombasa in Kenya as well as Entebbe in
Uganda.
</P>
<P>
It also flies to Djibouti, Eden in Yemen, Muscat in Oman and
Dubai in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
The ATC which has two Boeing 737s and one Fokker, also takes
passengers from Dar es Salaam to Lusaka, Harare and Johannesburg
in southern Africa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
