<HEADLINE> Eight Indonesian Mountain Climbers Die </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, February 25 (Xinhua) -- Eight Indonesians have died
from freezing weatures on Mount Rinjani on the eastern island of
Lombok, local reports said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The victims, two of whom were still missing, died Saturday and
Sunday as they were descending the 3,726-meter peak, east of Bali.
</P>
<P>
The climbers, five of them were aged between 50 and 60, were to
bathe in hot springs at the peak to cure diseases.
</P>
<P>
Rinjani, a dormant volcano, is popular as one of the most
scenic climbs of many volcanic mountains in the country. 
