<HEADLINE> Two Corporate Bonds Floated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 25 (Xinhua) -- Two batches of corporate bonds
became available for investors Monday, according to today's China
Daily.
</P>
<P>
They included 1.34 billion yuan (161 million US dollars) in
bond certificates issued by China Petrochemical Corp and one
billion yuan (120 million US dollars) in paperless bonds by Jilin
Chemical Industry Group (Jihua Group).
</P>
<P>
Officials with Guotai Securities Co, which underwrites the
petrochemical bonds and another one billion yuan (120 million US
dollars) in such bonds issued by the Ministry of Power Industry,
said that the bonds sold well and expected competition among the
bonds did not happen.
</P>
<P>
Floating of the power binds began on Friday. Before that, the
Ministry of Railway issued 3.5 billion yuan (421 million US
dollars) in such bonds in January.
</P>
<P>
An official with Citic Securities, one of the managers of the
Jihua bonds, said that he was satisfied with the first day's
issuance.
</P>
<P>
"Individual investors were attracted by the corporate bonds'
higher yield over the upcoming treasury bonds to be issued this
weekend," he said.
</P>
<P>
These corporate bonds are three-year bonds with an annual
interest rate of 11 percent compared to 8.46 percent for the new
issue of T-bonds for the same term.
</P>
<P>
The T-bonds, with a total amount of 123 billion yuan (14.8
billion US dollars), will go to market on Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
