<HEADLINE> Shanghai Stock Building to Begin Trial Use </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 25 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Stock Exchange
Building in central Pudong New Area is preparing for trial
operation in May, "China Daily" reported today.
</P>
<P>
The building's main developer, Shanghai Poly Real Estate
Development Co, a branch of the Beijing-based China Poly Group,
announced recently that the Shanghai Stock Exchange Building
Property Management Co, another branch of the Poly family, will be
in charge of sales and management of the exchange building, which
is being hailed as the future "Capital of the Stock Exchange" in
Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Construction work on the arch-shaped structure will be
completed in June, after which the Shanghai Stock Exchange (SSE)
will move from its current site in the bund in western Shanghai to
the new quarters.
</P>
<P>
Sales of office space in the SSE Building have been
satisfactory, company officials said, the 148-million-US-dollar
building has 27 storeys above ground level and three storeys
below.
</P>
<P>
During the past six months, 6,000 square meters of office
space, about 60 percent of the total, have been sold at 2,700 US
dollars per sq. m.
</P>
<P>
Most of the companies purchasing space in the building are
banks, financial institutions and securities brokerages from China
and abroad.
</P>
<P>
Negotiations have begun with other prospective tenants, such as
the Industrial Bank of Japan and the Shanghai Pudong Development
Bank.  
</P>
</TEXT>
