<HEADLINE> Malaysian PM Expresses Sadness over Deng Xiaoping's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
Demise
</P>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, February 25 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Prime Minister
Mahathir Mohamad today expressed his sadness over the demise of
Deng Xiaoping whom he described as "a great leader of China and
the world".
</P>
<P>
Mahathir visited the Chinese Embassy here to pay his last
respects to Deng Xiaoping who Mahathir met during his visit to
China in 1985.
</P>
<P>
Signing the condolence book, Mahathir wrote: "My condolence on
the demise of a truly great man and a great leader of China and
the world."
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters later, Mahathir said Deng Xiaoping was
"a great leader of China and he had brought about changes that no
other men could have been able to bring about".
</P>
<P>
Mahathir expressed his confidence that China will remember his
(Deng's) teachings and will make a success of what he taught
China.
</P>
<P>
Asked for his view on whether there will be any change in the
direction of China's economic reforms, he said "No, I don't think
so."
</P>
<P>
"There may be changes in style and forms, but there will be
no substantial changes," he added.
</P>
<P>
The Prime Minister was of the view that China's economic
reforms will continue.
</P>
<P>
On the future relations between China and Malaysia, Mahathir
said "the future will remain as good as it is now if not better
because we have established good contacts and relationship and
friendship with the present leaders of China."
</P>
<P>
During the last few days, Thousands of people from all walks
of life in Malaysia came to the Chinese Embassy here to pay their
last respects to Deng Xiaoping who died on last Wednesday.
</P>
</TEXT>
