<HEADLINE> Veteran Romanian Diplomats Mourn Deng's Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Veteran Romanian diplomats
joined the queue of countrymen to enter the Chinese Embassy here
to express their sorrow over the death of Chinese leader Deng
Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
Angelo Miculescu, ambassador to China from 1983 to 1990, cut
short his trip to Israel when he heard the news last week, in
order to return to Romania to mourn Deng's death at the Chinese
Embassy.
</P>
<P>
