many times. Deng's thought has become one of the most valuable
treasures for the world, he said.
</P>
<P>
Miculescu said he appreciated very much Deng's contribution to
the development of relations between Romania and China and China's
economic assistance to Romania.
</P>
<P>
Teordor Melescanu, former Romanian Foreign Minister in
1992-96, and Romulus Budura, former ambassador to China in
1990-95, went to the embassy for the second time to pay tributes.
</P>
<P>
Budura said Deng's death was a great loss to China, but his
thought has become a spiritual pillar for the country. 
