<HEADLINE> Chilean, Swedish Navy Commanders Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Cooperation between the
Swedish and Chilean navies is excellent, Rear Admiral Peter
Nordbeck, visiting commander in chief of the Swedish navy, said
here today.
</P>
<P>
Nordbeck made the remarks after holding talks with his Chilean
counterpart, Admiral Jorge Martinez Busch.
</P>
<P>
Nordbeck arrived here Sunday on an official visit. The main
aims of his trip are to gain first-hand knowledge of facilities,
operating capacities and logistics of the Chilean navy and to
strengthen ties between the two navies.
</P>
<P>
The Swedish navy also decided to donate a ship, the "Alsvorg"
to the Chilean navy. On arrival in May, it will be renamed
"Almirante Merino." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
