<HEADLINE> China to Carry Forward Deng's Behest: Jiang (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 25 (Xinhua) -- Jiang Zemin, general secretary
of the Communist Party of China's Central Committee, said here
today that under the strong leadership of the Party Central
Committee, the whole Party, the whole army, and the people of
various ethnic groups across China will certainly push forward the
great cause of building socialism with Chinese characteristics
pioneered by Comrade Deng Xiaoping and build the country into a
socialist and modernized country which is strong, prosperous,
democratic, and civilized.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, also Chinese President and chairman of the Central
Military Commission, made these remarks at a memorial meeting for
Comrade Deng Xiaoping, who passed away in Beijing last Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
At the memorial meeting, which was held at the Great Hall of
the People, Jiang said that the Party Central Committee called on
the whole Party, the whole army, and the people of all ethnic
groups of the whole country to turn grief into strength, carry on
the will of Comrade Deng Xiaoping, and express the mourning by
working harder and doing well in all aspects of practical work.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said: Deng Xiaoping was among founders of the people's
republic, and after the founding of the People's Republic of China
(PRC), he became an important member of the Communist Party of
China's first generation of the central collective leadership with
Comrade Mao Zedong at the core. After the third plenum of the 11th
CPC Central Committee, he became the core of the Communist Party
of China's second generation of central collective leadership and
led us to pioneer a new road of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics. Comrade Deng Xiaoping said that without Comrade
Mao Zedong, we Chinese people would have to grope in the dark for
at least a longer period of time. And likewise, we should say
today that without Comrade Deng Xiaoping, the Chinese people would
not live a new life like today's and there would not be today's
new situation of reforms and opening-up and the bright prospects
of the socialist modernization.
</P>
</TEXT>
