<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chicago's Pippen Named NBA Player of Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Scottie Pippen of the Chicago
Bulls edged Charlotte's Anthony Mason on Monday for NBA Player of
the Week honors for games played from February 17 to 23.
</P>
<P>
Pippen paced the Bulls to a 3-0 record by averaging 32.3 points
for the week, the second-highest total in the league. He added 6.6
rebounds and 5.3 assists per game to go along with 37-for-63
shooting from the field, 7-for-18 shooting from three-point range
and 16-of-17 shooting from the free throw line.
</P>
<P>
Chicago (48-6) has won six straight games, and is tied with
Detroit and Seattle for the league's longest active winning
streaks. On pace to match last season's history-making 72-10
record, the Bulls lead Detroit (40-13) by 7 and a half games in
the Central Division.
</P>
<P>
Pippen started the week with a career-high 47 points, five
rebounds, four assists and two steals in 41 minutes of Chicago's
134-123 win over Denver. He followed it up with 28 points, 10
rebounds, seven assists and three steals in the Bulls' 103-99 win
at Washington and had 22 points in his team's 120-87 win over
Golden State.
</P>
<P>
Mason helped guide the Hornets (34-21) to a 4-0 week and to
within two games of the Atlanta Hawks (35-18) in the Central
Division. He averaged 23.5 points on .725 shooting from the field
(37-51) and .714 from the free throw line (20-28). Mason also
grabbed 10.5 rebounds per game and recorded 7.3 assists and 2.00
steals per contest. His season-high 28 points in Charlotte's
124-110 win over Orlando included a team-record 11-for-11 shooting
performance.
</P>
<P>
Other candidates for NBA Player of the Week were Boston's
Antoine Walker, Charlotte's Glen Rice, Cleveland's Tyrone Hill,
Los Angeles Lakers' Elden Campbell, Miami's Tim Hardaway,
Orlando's Horace Grant, Philadelphia's Derrick Coleman, Seattle's
Gary Payton and Utah's Karl Malone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
