<HEADLINE> Sino-US Aircraft Spare Parts Manufacturing Facility Started </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, February 25 (Xinhua) -- Work on a Sino-US aircraft spare
parts manufacturing center, involving a total investment of 200
million yuan, began recently at Xi'an Aeronautical Engine Company
(XAE) in northwest China's Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
The center will be jointly backed by the XAE and the US's
General Electric Company (GE) and have a floor space of 8,600 sq
m. Construction is scheduled to be completed this November.
</P>
<P>
According to officials in charge of the project, the company
will be able to have an output worth 50 million U.S. dollars a
year when it goes into operation.
</P>
<P>
XAE has a 40-year history and has supplied foreign companies
with 20 kinds of engines and related spare parts and has been
chosen by several foreign companies as sole supplier of 99
different kinds of spare parts.
</P>
<P>
The company has cooperated with GE for a decade and has
provided it with 2,500 low-pressure turbine disks of six types,
with total orders worth 34 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The company has earned 15 million U.S. dollars from annual
exports for three years and has done 150 million U.S. dollars
worth of business. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
