<HEADLINE> Chinese Newspaper Highlights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 25 (Xinhua) -- All major Beijing-based
newspapers today give full coverage to China's bidding farewell to
Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
"People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- A banner headline reads: "Eternal glory to our beloved
Comrade Deng Xiaoping." The front page reports that leading
officials of the Communist Party of China and the Chinese
Government and over 100,000 people in Beijing paid final respects
to Comrade Deng Xiaoping yesterday. Seniors leaders Jiang Zemin,
Li Peng, Qiao Shi, Li Ruihuan, Zhu Rongji, Liu Huaqing, Hu Jintao
and Rong Yiren presented wreaths and paid last respects to Deng
and escorted his body to the cemetery for cremation.
</P>
<P>
-- The front page carries three photos: one of Deng lying in
state amidst flowers, evergreens, and cypresses, appearing to be
at peace. Another shows Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, Qiao Shi, Li
Ruihuan, Zhu Rongji, Liu Huaqing, Hu Jintao, Rong Yiren, and
Deng's family members and relatives bidding farewell to Deng. The
third shows Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, and others expressing sympathy
for Zhuo Lin, Deng's widow.
</P>
<P>
-- The paper devotes an entire page to nine photos of people
from all walks of life in Beijing standing along Chang'an Avenue
to say goodbye to Deng.
</P>
<P>
-- More than a million pictures of Deng have been printed to
meet the sudden demand all over the country for pictures of him
since last Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
 "Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- leading officials and ordinary people across China pledged
that they will turn grief into strength and adhere to the party's
basic line for years to come.
</P>
<P>
-- A solemn memorial meeting for the late Chinese leader Deng
Xiaoping will be held at the Great Hall of the People today. The
meeting will be telecast live to both domestic and overseas
audiences.
</P>
<P>
-- Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, and other Chinese senior leaders
visited Deng when he was hospitalized in critical condition and
after his passing, and extended sympathy to his family in various
ways.
</P>
<P>
-- Members of the press in Beijing held a meeting yesterday to
recall the memory of Deng Xiaoping and pledged to conscientiously
study Deng's theory of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics and to make it better known publicly.
</P>
<P>
"Economic Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- A million post and telecommunications workers have been
mourning Deng's death with a deep sense of grief and have voiced
their determination to speed up the development of
telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
-- One article describes Deng's three important speeches on the
relations between the market economy and progress in ideology and
ethics.
</P>
<P>
"China Youth Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- More than 100,000 people from Beijing and other parts of
China lined the two-and-a-half kilometer route along Beijing's
Chang'an Avenue yesterday as the hearse carrying Deng's casket
moved slowly towards Babaoshan Revolutionary Cemetery from the PLA
General Hospital.
</P>
<P>
-- Leaders of the Chinese Communist Youth League, the All-China
Youth Federation, and All-China Students' Federation recalled
Deng's great sense of care for the country's young people.
</P>
<P>
-- Under a banner headline reading, "Say hello to Xiaoping
again and see Xiaoping off", the paper devotes an entire page to
photos of scenes of Chinese bidding farewell to Deng.  
</P>
</TEXT>
