<HEADLINE> Solemn Memorial Meeting Held for Deng Xiaoping (7) Eds: updated with end of the memorial meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 25 (Xinhua) -- A large, solemn memorial
meeting has just concluded this morning at the Great Hall of the
People for Comrade Deng Xiaoping, who passed away last Wednesday
at the age of 93.
</P>
<P>
A total of 10,000 people, including members of the Funeral
Committee (some members from outside Beijing have sent
representatives), representatives of the Party and government
institutions, army headquarters, people's organizations, and
people from all walks of life in the Chinese capital, Deng's
friends and representatives from his hometown took part in
the service which was telecast live for both domestic and
overseas audiences.
</P>
<P>
The rostrum of the main hall had a silver-grey backdrop, with
a large color portrait of Deng, 5.2 meters high and 4 meters wide,
hanging in the middle. Deng's casket was covered with the flag of
the Communist Party of China and was placed amidst bouquets of
flowers and sprigs of evergreens and cypress.
</P>
<P>
A floral arrangement presented by relatives of Comrade Deng
was placed in front of the casket. On both sides of the rostrum
were wreaths sent by the CPC Central Committee, the Standing
Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC), the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC), the Central Military Commission, the
Revolutionary Committee of the Chinese Kuomintang, Chinese
Democratic League, Chinese Association for Promoting Democracy,
Chinese Peasants and Workers Democratic Party, the China Zhi Gong
Party, Jiu San Society, and Taiwan Democratic Self-Government
League.
</P>
<P>
There were also wreaths presented by China's party and
government leaders, people without any party affiliation, the
All-China Federation of Industry and Commerce, various people's
organizations, and people from various walks of life in the
Chinese capital on both sides of the rostrum.
</P>
</TEXT>
