<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Solemn Memorial Meeting Held for Deng Xiaoping (8) Eds: updated with end of the memorial meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At 10:00, Premier Li Peng, who is a member of the Standing
Committee of the CPC Central Committee, proclaimed the opening of
the Memorial Meeting for Comrade Deng Xiaoping. Whistles on
trains, ships, warships, and in factories across the country
sounded for three minutes, in tribute to the venerable leader.
</P>
<P>
Following Premier Li's opening of the meeting, President Jiang
Zemin, who is general secretary of the CPC Central Committee,
spoke to the assembled gathering.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who is also chairman of the Central Military Commission,
called Comrade Deng Xiaoping "an outstanding leader whose immense
prestige was recognized by the whole Party, the whole army, and
the people of all ethnic groups throughout China." Jiang said that
Deng was a great Marxist, a great proletarian revolutionary,
statesman, military strategist, and diplomat, and a battle-tested
Communist fighter, the chief architect of China's socialist
reforms, opening-up, and modernization drive, and the founder of
the theory of building socialism with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
After Jiang's speech, all present bowed three times to Comrade
Deng to express their feelings of reverence and to honor the
memory of his more than 70-year-long revolutionary career, his
leadership and victory in China's new democratic revolution, the
founding of New China, and the establishment, consolidation and
development of the Chinese cause of socialism.
</P>
<P>
The conclusion of the memorial meeting was accompanied by the
music of "the Internationale". Jiang and the other Chinese leaders
shook hands with Zhuo Lin, Deng's widow, and with his sons and
daughters and expressed their condolences.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
