<HEADLINE> Cuba, US to Increase Exchanges Over AIDS </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Doctors and experts from Cuba
and the United States specializing in AIDS will increase
scientific exchanges on the disease.
</P>
<P>
The one-year exchanges will include a visit to New York by a
Cuban doctor and nurse to train in the specialized treatment of
this disease.
</P>
<P>
On August 6-13, a conference with the theme, "Building bridges
and crossing frontiers", will be held in Havana. It will be
attended by people from the medical and scientific communities and
people afflicted with AIDS, from the U,S., Cuba and several Latin
America nations.
</P>
<P>
During 1986 and January 1997, there were 1,476 people diagnosed
as HIV positive in Cuba. Of these. 592 have AIDS and 392 have
died from the disease. 
</P>
</TEXT>
