<HEADLINE> OPEC Oil Prices Continue to fall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, February 24 (Xinhua) -- The average price of OPEC's
basket of seven crude oils fell last week to 20.22 U.S. dollars
per barrel, representing a 35-cent decline over the previous week.
</P>
<P>
According to the OPEC Secretariat, the average oil price in
January as a whole stood at 23.19 dollars a barrel, 32 cents
higher than last December.
</P>
<P>
The internal reference price set by the organization is 21
dollars per barrel. 
</P>
