<HEADLINE> Solemn Memorial Meeting to be Held Deng Xiaoping (4) Eds: updated with presence of Deng's relatives, top Chinese leaders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 25 (Xinhua) -- A large, solemn memorial
meeting will be held at ten o'clock this morning at the Great Hall
of the People for comrade Deng Xiaoping, who passed away last
Wednesday at the age of 93.
</P>
<P>
A total of 10,000 people, including members of the Funeral
Committee (some members from outside Beijing have sent
representatives), representatives of the Communist Party of China
(CPC) Central Committee, government, military and people's
organizations, and people from all walks of life in the Chinese
capital, Deng's friends, and representatives from his hometown
will take part in the service which is telecast live to both
domestic and overseas audiences.
</P>
<P>
 The rostrum of the meeting hall has a silver-grey backdrop,
with a large color portrait of Deng, 5.2 meters high and 4 meters
wide, hanging in the middle. Deng's casket is covered with the
flag of the Communist Party of China and placed amidst bouquets of
flowers and sprigs of evergreens and cypress.
</P>
<P>
A floral arrangement presented by relatives of Comrade Deng is
placed in front of the casket. On both sides of the rostrum are
wreaths sent by the CPC Central Committee, the Standing Committee
of the National People's Congress, the National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference, the Central
Military Commission, the Revolutionary Committee of the Chinese
Kuomintang, Chinese Democratic League, Chinese Association for
Promoting Democracy, Chinese Peasants and Workers Democratic
Party, the China Zhi Gong Party, Jiu San Society, and Taiwan
Democratic Self-Government League.
</P>
<P>
There are also wreaths presented by China's top party and state
leaders, people without any party affiliation, the All-China
Federation of Industry and Commerce, various people's
organizations, and people from various walks of life in the
Chinese capital on both sides of the rostrum.
</P>
<P>
At 9:45 A.M., the curtain of the Great Hall of the People's
main hall was raised and all present at the service rose in
silence. Comrade Deng's relatives were led down to the front of
the hall. Party and state leaders Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, Qiao Shi,
Li Ruihuan, Zhu Rongji, Liu Huaqing, Hu Jintao and Rong Yiren,
wearing the traditional white paper flowers and black armbands,
sat in the front row.  
</P>
</TEXT>
