<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970225.0205 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang's Speech at Deng's Memorial Meeting (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Comrade Deng Xiaoping was an outstanding leader whose high
prestige was recognized by the Party, the military, and the
people of all ethnic groups throughout China. He was a great
Marxist, a great proletarian revolutionary, statesman, military
strategist and diplomat, and a long tested communist fighter,
the chief architect of China's socialist reforms, opening-up,
and modernization drive, and the founder of the theory of
building socialism with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
In the history of the Communist Party of China, the Party led
the Chinese people to carry out a great revolution to turn the
semi-colonial and semi-feudal old China into the socialist new
China, and has, since the third plenum of the 11th CPC Central
Committee, led the people to start a new revolution, that is to
turn China from a undeveloped socialist country into a prosperous,
democratic and civilized socialist modern country. In the course
of the two great revolutions, two historic leaps were achieved in the
combination of Marxism with China's realities and
two major theoretical findings were made, namely, the Mao Zedong
thought and Deng Xiaoping's theory on building socialism with
Chinese characteristics. The two great revolutions and the two
historic leaps made two great men, namely, Comrade Mao Zedong
and Comrade Deng Xiaoping, who was a comrade-in-arms of Comrade
Mao Zedong's and a successor to Comrade Mao Zedong's cause.
</P>
<P>
In a large semi-colonial and semi-feudal oriental country like
the old China, there were no ready answers for the communists to
lead revolutions to victory and they must open up their own
road. And this was a road of armed struggle, as well as a road of
establishing revolutionary bases in rural areas, encircling cities
from the countryside and eventually winning the nationwide
political power. This road was pioneered by our Party led by
Comrade Mao Zedong. Following the road unswervingly, comrade Deng
Xiaoping launched Uprisings in Guangxi, founded Red Army units,
and established revolutionary bases. After he arrived in the
Central Revolutionary Base, he was removed from his post by the
"Left" leaders within the Party for supporting Comrade Mao
Zedong's correct line. This was the first setback he had suffered
in his political career. During the Long March, he attended the
Zunyi Meeting, which marked a significant turn in the Party's
history.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970225.0206 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Solemn Memorial Meeting Being Held for Deng Xiaoping (6) Eds: updated with speech by Jiang Zemin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 25 (Xinhua) -- A large, solemn memorial
meeting is being held this morning at the Great Hall of the People
for comrade Deng Xiaoping, who passed away last Wednesday at the
age of 93.
</P>
<P>
A total of 10,000 people, including members of the Funeral
Committee (some members from outside Beijing have sent
representatives), representatives of Party and government
institutions, army headquarters, people's organizations, and
