<DOCNO> XIE19970225.0207 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang's Speech at Deng's Memorial Meeting (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
During the War of Resistance Against Japan and the following
War of Liberation, Comrade Deng Xiaoping together with Comrade Liu
Bocheng jointly led the troops, always working in key positions of
the overall strategic situation, and waging tit-for-tat struggles
against the enemies on the foremost front, and always firmly
carrying out major strategic decisions by Comrade Mao Zedong,
showing no fears of difficulties and dangers, and bravely
shouldering heavy responsibilities. He served successively as
political commissar of the 129th Division and secretary of the
Taihang Sub-Bureau of the Northern Bureau of the CPC Central
Committee, and acting secretary of the Northern Bureau of the CPC
Central Committee, took charge of the work of the Eighth Route
Army headquarters, and established and led the anti-Japanese bases
in the enemy's rear areas in north China.
</P>
<P>
At the Seventh National Congress of the CPC, he was elected
member of the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
When the civil war broke out, he served successively as
political commissar of the Shanxi-Hebei-Shandong-Henan Military
Area Command, the first secretary of the Central China Plains
Bureau of the CPC Central Committee, and political commissar
of the Central China Plains Field Army.
</P>
<P>
In a display of dauntless heroism, he and Comrade Liu Bocheng
jointly led their troops to shift the fighting from internal
lines to external lines, forced their way across the Yellow River,
and marched hundreds of kilometers to the Dabie Mountains,
ushering in the beginning of the strategic offensive in the
People's War of Liberation.
</P>
<P>
During the period of the decisive campaign of strategic
significance, he served as secretary of the General Front
Committee, which exercised unified command over the Central China
Plains Field Army and the East China Field Army, and first
secretary of the East China Bureau of the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Along with other leaders of the two field armies, he led the
Huaihai Campaign, the largest of the three decisive campaigns,
the campaign of crossing the Yangtze River, and the liberation
of Nanjing, Shanghai, and various provinces in southeast China,
which declared the downfall of the Kuomintang's reactionary rule.
</P>
<P>
Then he led the troops to march into the southwest, and took
part in leading the peaceful liberation of Tibet, completing the
liberation of the Chinese mainland. Comrade Deng Xiaoping scored
illustrious military exploits for the founding of New China.
</P>
</TEXT>
