<DOCNO> XIE19970225.0208 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang's Speech at Deng's Memorial Meeting (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Following the founding of the People's Republic of China, our
Party faced the task of how to transit from new democracy to
socialism, and of probing its own road of building socialism
under the comparatively backward economic and cultural
conditions. The Party led the people in achieving great
successes, but also made some mistakes.
</P>
<P>
Comrade Deng Xiaoping was transferred to Beijing from the
southwest to join in the central leadership, served
successively as vice-premier of the Government Administration
Council, secretary-general of the CPC Central Committee, and
vice-premier of the State Council, and was elected to the
Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee at the fifth plenum
of the seventh CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
In his report on revising the Party's Constitution at the
eighth CPC National Congress, he put forward and profoundly
expounded the Party's task of strengthening the building of itself
as a ruling party. At the first plenum of the Eighth CPC Central
Committee, he was elected member of the Standing Committee of the
Political Bureau, and general-secretary, of the CPC Central
Committee.
</P>
<P>
During the ten years when he served as the general-secretary,
he shouldered heavy tasks, put forth many correct proposals, and
carried out fruitful work in establishing the socialist system,
conducting socialist construction, probing a socialist road that
suits China's situation, and in overcoming the economic
difficulties in the three years, which were mainly caused by
"Leftist" errors, through summing up experience, correcting
mistakes, and readjusting policies.
</P>
</TEXT>
