<HEADLINE> Austrian Senior Leaders, UN Representatives Mourn Deng's Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Senior Austrian leaders and
United Nations representatives in Vienna went to the Chinese
Embassy on Monday to express their condolences over Deng
Xiaoping's death.
</P>
<P>
The President of the Austrian National Council Heinz Fischer
told reporters after the mourning ceremony that Deng was renowned
throughout the world and China had lost an outstanding statesman
and reformer.
</P>
<P>
Defense Minister Werner Fasslabend wrote on the mourning book
that "the death of every great statesman is beyond the border of
his own country and Deng's death has a bearing on the whole
world. He led China onto the track of development, prosperity and
standing in the world. I, along with Chinese people, feel
great regret over Deng's death and I hope that China will keep its
stability, peace and prosperity."
</P>
<P>
Other senior leaders, including Foreign Ministry
Secretary-General Albert Rohan, the Presidential Office Director
Georg Hennig, as well as UN Under-Secretary-General and
Director-General of the UN Office in Vienna Giorgio Giacomelli,
the UN Industrial Development Organization Director-General
Mauricio Campos and International Atomic Energy Agency
Director-General Hans Blix also went to the embassy to express
their condolences over Deng's death. 
</P>
