<HEADLINE> Jiang's Speech at Deng's Memorial Meeting (10) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
With political upheavals occurring both domestically and
internationaly at the end of the 1980s and the beginning of the
1990s, our Party faced another major historical juncture. Under
the firm and strong support of Comrade Deng Xiaoping and other
senior comrades, and relying on the people, the Party and the
Government adhered to the four Cardinal Principles with a
clear-cut stand, and safeguarded the independence, dignity,
security and stability of the nation while unswervingly persisting
in taking economic construction as the focus and in reform and
opening up.
</P>
<P>
Because the Party and the Government adopted a firm and sober
stand and because the achievements of reform and opening up and
socialist modernization had taken root in the hearts of the
people, we withstood the severe test, and our cause continued its
vigorous development along the road set by the Third Plenary
Session of the 11th CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Comrade Deng Xiaoping had long favored the abolishment of
cadres' life-long tenure system. He himself expressed the sincere
wish for retirement several times. The 13th CPC National Congress
agreed with him that he only retain the official post as chairman
of the Central Military Commission, and the Fifth Plenary Session
of the 13th CPC Central Committee agreed with his resignation from
this post.
</P>
<P>
Comrade Deng Xiaoping created full conditions and played a
crucial role for the smooth transition from the second generation
central collective leadership to the new central collective
leadership, ensuring stability of the Party and the State.
</P>
</TEXT>
