<HEADLINE> Jiang's Speech at Deng's Memorial Meeting (11) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Although he retired from the leading post, Comrade Deng
Xiaoping, with a strong sense of historic responsibility,
continued to pay close attention to China's reform, opening up to
the outside world and the modernization drive. The important
remarks he made during his tour of southern China in early 1992
represent a scientific summing-up of the Party's basic practices
and experiences since the Third Plenary Session of the Eleventh
Party Central Committee in 1978, as well as an in-depth
theoretical answer to many major cognitive issues which had long
perplexed and trammeled people's thinking. Deng's talks not only
played an important guiding role in ensuring the successful
convening of the Party's 14th national congress, but is of a
far-reaching significance for the entire cause of socialist
modernization as well.
</P>
<P>
Comrade Deng Xiaoping's talks of the southern tour and the
Party's 14th national congress marked the beginning of a new phase
for China's socialist reform, opening-up and the modernization
drive. The 89-year-old Comrade Deng Xiaoping personally took
charge of the compiling of the third volume of "Selected Works of
Deng Xiaoping", finalizing the book article by article. The third
and second volumes of "Selected Works of Deng Xiaoping" contained
important works characterized by Comrade Deng Xiaoping's
originality during the formation and the development of the theory
of building socialism with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
</TEXT>
