<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Urges Changes in Cabinet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
Monday urged Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin to reshuffle the
cabinet to improve its efficiency.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with Chernomyrdin in the Kremlin, Yeltsin said
he was worried that many people are dissatisfied with the government
and the president because of the country's difficult economic
situation and the government's inability to cope with the problem
of delayed wages and pensions.
</P>
<P>
He criticized the government's social achievements and called
on Chernomyrdin to propose changes in the cabinet to make it "more
flexible, more efficient and more able to solve problems".
</P>
<P>
The government owes workers billions of rubles in backpay,
pensions and social benefits, even though Yeltsin had promised to
radically improve the situation before he suffered from double
pneumonia earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin promised that all delayed payments would be fully
repaid by July.
</P>
<P>
However, he argued that his cabinet was "sorting things out",
and said regional authorities were partly to blame for the social
problems in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
