<HEADLINE> Yugoslav Leaders Mourn Death of Deng </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Major General Momcilo
Perisic, Chief of General Staff of the Army of the Federal
Republic of Yugoslavia, went to the Chinese Embassy here today to
mourn the death of Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
Perisic noted in the book of mourning that Deng made great
contributions to the organization and construction of the armed
forces in China.
</P>
<P>
Deng enjoyed great prestige and authority among the Chinese
military, making him one of the great leaders of the 20th century.
</P>
<P>
Human Rights Minister Margit Savovic also went to the Chinese
Embassy to mourn Deng, who passed away last Wednesday in Beijing
at the age of 93. Mirk Marjanovic, Prime Minister of the Republic
of Serbia, went to the embassy on Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
