<HEADLINE> Chilean Officials Mourn Deng's Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Chilean Vice President Carlos
Figueroa and Jose Joaquin Brunner, acting foreign and defense
minister, today expressed their condolences to the Chinese embassy
here over Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping's death.
</P>
<P>
Figueroa, who also serves as interior minister, and Brunner,
remained silent before the portrait of Deng Xiaoping placed in the
mourning hall of the diplomatic mission and expressed their
condolences to Chinese Ambassador Wang Chengjia.
</P>
<P>
Deng Xiaoping, a great proletarian revolutionary, statesman,
strategist and diplomat, passed away on February 19 in Beijing at
the age of 93.
</P>
<P>
The two ministers signed the book of condolences to express
"the feelings of sorrow".
</P>
<P>
Figueroa told Xinhua that he "wanted to reiterate our
expression of solidarity and sorrow over the death of the most
important leader of the Chinese nation on behalf of the Chilean
government and people."
</P>
<P>
The acting foreign minister also expressed, in the name of the
Chilean Foreign Ministry, sorrow and solidarity "over the sad
death of this leader who has meant so much for the People's
Republic of China and for the relations between your country and
Chile."
</P>
<P>
Diplomatic representations in Chile, representatives of Chinese
companies and residents also went to the Chinese embassy to pay
their respects to Deng Xiaoping. 
</P>
</TEXT>
