<HEADLINE> Russia, Vietnam to Cement Bilateral Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Speaker of Russia's State Duma
(the lower house) Gennady n. Seleznyov told a press conference
here this evening that he and Vietnamese leaders agreed to restore
and enhance the traditional ties between Russia and Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
Seleznyov, who arrived here last Saturday for a five-day
official visit, held talks with Vietnamese National Assembly
Chairman Nong Duc Manh and was received by Vietnamese Communisty
Party Leader Do Muoi and Prime Minister Vo Van Kiet.
</P>
<P>
The two sides expressed their satisfaction at the development
of the traditional ties and decided to further promoted and
boosted, contributing to the enhancement of peace and cooperation
in the Asian-pacific region and the world as a whole in accordance
with the common trend of peace and cooperation for development.
</P>
<P>
The speaker said he did not discuss with Vietnamese leader the
debt issue between the two countries, adding that this problem
would be resolved by the two governments.
</P>
<P>
Asked about the armes sales to Vietnam, Seleznyov confirmed
that the two countries will continue their military
cooperation. But he gave no details.
</P>
<P>
The speaker also said Russia hopes to expand cooperation with
ASEAN.
</P>
<P>
Seleznyov is scheduled to leave Hanoi for Ho Chi Minh city
Tuesday and conclude his Vietnam trip on Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
