<HEADLINE> Eds: updated with scences of the meeting hall Solemn Memorial Meeting to Be Held for Deng Xiaoping (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 25 (Xinhua) -- A large, solemn memorial
meeting will be held at ten o'clock this morning at the Great Hall
of the People for Comrade Deng Xiaoping, who passed away last
Wednesday at the age of 93.
</P>
<P>
A total of 10,000 people, including members of the Funeral
Committee (some members from outside Beijing have sent
representatives), representatives of the Central Party and
government institutions, army headquarters, people's
organizations, and people from all walks of life in the Chinese
capital, Deng's friends, and representatives from his hometown
will take part in the service which will be telecast live for
domestic and overseas audiences.
</P>
<P>
The main hall of the Great Hall of the People has an air of
solemnity about it. Above the rostrum hangs a large banner bearing
the slogan "Memorial Meeting of Comrade Deng Xiaoping". Two
banners hang from the balconies of the second and third floors
of the main hall.
</P>
<P>
One is inscribed with the words "Eternal Glory to Comrade Deng
Xiaoping who enjoys the love and esteem of the people of the whole
Party, the whole army and people of all ethnic groups throught the
country." The other exhorts people to "Carry forward the behest of
Comrade Deng Xiaoping and advance the great cause of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics under the leadership of the
CPC Central Committee with Comrade Jiang Zemin at the core."
</P>
