<HEADLINE> Solemn Memorial Meeting to be Held Deng Xiaoping (2) Eds: updated with more scenes of the meeting hall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 25 (Xinhua) -- A large, solemn memorial
meeting will be held at ten o'clock this morning at the Great Hall
of the People for Comrade Deng Xiaoping, who passed away last
Wednesday at the age of 93.
</P>
<P>
A total of 10,000 people, including members of the Funeral
Committee (some members from outside Beijing have sent
representatives), representatives of the Party and government
institutions, army headquarters, people's organizations, and
people from all walks of life in the Chinese capital, Deng's friends,
and representatives from his hometown will take part in the
service which will be telecast live to both domestic and overseas
audiences.
</P>
<P>
The rostrum of the meeting hall has a silver-grey backdrop,
with a large color portrait of Deng Xiaoping, 5.2 meters high and
4 meters wide, hanging in the middle. Deng's casket is covered
with the flag of the Communist Party of China and has been placed
amidst bouquets of flowers and sprigs of evergreens and cypress.
 
</P>
