<HEADLINE> Solemn Memorial Meeting to be Held Deng Xiaoping (3) Eds: updated with floral arrangement in the meeting hall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 25 (Xinhua) -- A large, solemn memorial
meeting will be held at ten o'clock this morning at the Great Hall
of the People for comrade Deng Xiaoping, who passed away last
Wednesday at the age of 93.
</P>
<P>
A total of 10,000 people, including members of the Funeral
Committee (some members from outside Beijing have sent
representatives), representatives of Party and government
institutions, army headquarters, people's organizations, and
people from all walks of life in the Chinese capital, Deng's
friends and representatives from his hometown will take part in
the service which will be telecast live to both domestic and
overseas audiences.
</P>
<P>
The rostrum of the meeting hall has a silver-grey
backdrop. With a large color portrait of Deng, 5.2 meters high and
4 meters wide, hanging in the middle. Deng's casket is covered
with the flag of the Communist Party of China and has been placed
amidst bouquets of flowers and sprigs of evergreens and cypress.
</P>
<P>
A floral arrangement presented by relatives of Comrade Deng
is placed in front of the casket. On both sides of the rostrum
are wreaths sent by the CPC Central Committee, the Standing
Committee of the National People's Congress, the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference, the Central Military Commission, the Revolutionary
Committee of the Chinese Kuomintang, Chinese Democratic League,
Chinese Association for Promoting Democracy, Chinese Peasants and
Workers Democratic Party, the China Zhi Gong Party, Jiu San
Society, and Taiwan Democratic Self-Government League.
</P>
<P>
There are also wreaths presented by China's top party and state
leaders, people without any party affiliation, the All-China
Federation of Industry and Commerce, various people's
organizations, and people from various walks of life in the
Chinese capital on both sides of the rostrum.  
</P>
