<HEADLINE> Fire Sweeps Through Central Jakarta Neighborhood </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, February 25 (Xinhua) -- Fire swept through houses in a
crowded neighborhood in Pejompongan, central Jakarta, capital of
Indonesia, last night.
</P>
<P>
The fire injured one resident and destroyed at least 13 houses,
spokesman of the Central Jakarta Fire Brigade Aminudin said today.
</P>
<P>
Some 15 fire trucks were deployed and the blaze was put out
after about an hour, he said.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the fire is still being determined.  
</P>
