<HEADLINE> Former World Champion to Sue Pop Singer for Damages </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Former world champion Patrik
Sjoberg said on Monday he was to file charges against a woman pop
singer who smashed his face in a nightclub row last week.
</P>
<P>
High jumper Sjoberg had nine stitches after the singer smashed
her glass in his face on Friday night, and had to skip the indoor
athletics meeting in Birmingham on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Sjoberg said the row broke out when he asked the 21-year-old
woman to stop spilling beer on him but she laughed and allegedly
smashed a glass in his face instead.
</P>
<P>
However, the woman had her version of the story, claiming that
Sjoberg spilt champagne on her dress and refused to apologise.
</P>
</TEXT>
