<HEADLINE> Former Bodybuilding Winner Jailed for Steroid Conspiracy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Massimo Merighi, the 1993
winner of the Mr. World Body-Building Competition, will be jailed
for five months for conspiracy in possessing and distributing
anabolic steroids, reports reaching here said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Besides, Merighi, the 32-year-old Italian body-builder who
lives in Los Angeles, was also sentenced to two months in a
community center and two years of supervised release as well as a
fine of 800 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dated back to February 1994, Merighi and compatriot Andrea
Greco brought in between 20,000 and 34,000 U.S. dollars worth of
anabolic steroids from Italy into the United States.
</P>
<P>
Merighi sold them to Massimo Avidano, a former body builder and
model who is currently a trainer in Venice, California. The
steroids were also found to be distributed in Los Angeles and San
Francisco.
</P>
<P>
Adviano, 35, was also sentenced to five months in prison and
fined 5,000 U.S. dollars, two years of supervised release and 400
hours of community service. 
</P>
</TEXT>
