<HEADLINE> Solemn Memorial Meeting to Be Held for Deng Xiaoping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 25 (Xinhua) -- A large, solemn memorial
meeting will be held this morning at the Great Hall of the People
for Comrade Deng Xiaoping, who passed away last Wednesday at the
age of 93.
</P>
<P>
The memorial meeting is held by the Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China, the Standing Committee of the National
People's Congress, the State Council, the National Committee of
the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference and the
Central Military Commission.
</P>
<P>
A total of 10,000 people, including members of the Funeral
Committee, (some members from outside Beijing have sent their
representatives), representatives of the Central Party and
government institutions and army headquarters, people's
organizations, and people from all walks of life in the capital,
Deng's friends, and representatives from his hometown, will take
part in the service.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will be telecast live by the China Central
Broadcasting Station, China Radio International and China Central
Television Station (CCTV), and will be viewed by the entire
nation. Whistles on trains, ships, warships, and in factories will
be sounded for three minutes at ten o'clock when the memorial
meeting begins, in tribute to the venerable leader.
</P>
<P>
The remains of Comrade Deng Xiaoping were cremated at the
Babaoshan Revolutionary Cemetery in west Beijing on Monday
morning. 
</P>
</TEXT>
