relations, including the probe into the June 25, 1996, truck
bombing at Khobar Tower, Dhahran, which killed 19 American
servicemen, will be at the top of the agenda.
</P>
<P>
The Middle East peace process, Gulf security and oil supplies
would also be discussed, the U.S. officials said.
</P>
<P>
However, the issue of whether the Saudis plan to buy 100 F-16
aircraft from the United States, a deal reported to be worth
billions of dollars, would not come up, they said.
</P>
<P>
Davies said the United States was likely to maintain its
military presence in the Gulf for some time to come for its direct
interest.
</P>
<P>
"The United States has a direct interest in the security of the
Gulf region, so we're going to be there in a fairly serious way
for the foreseeable future," he said. 
