<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, February 24 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Secretary of Commerce
William Daley today went to the Chinese Embassy in Washington to
mourn Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping who passed away last week.
</P>
<P>
Daley observed a-minute silence before the picture of Deng in
the mourning hall in the embassy.
</P>
<P>
"On behalf of the Department of Commerce, I express deep
condolences to the Chinese people," Daley told Xinhua after the
ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The secretary said Deng Xiaoping was "a visionary person" who
has been strengthened the relationship between China and the
United States and many other countries throughout the world.
</P>
