On the trade relations between China and the United States,
Daley said, "Our relations are improving."
</P>
<P>
"My goal is to make sure that the relationships, which are
strengthened in the last couple of years, are strengthened and
improved," said Daley, who is going to visit China within a few
days.
</P>
<P>
The secretary expected further development in trade and
economic ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Also went to the Chinese Embassy to mourn Deng today were
former U.S. president George Bush and Senators Akaka and Dianne
Feinstein. 
