<HEADLINE> Rural Credit Agencies to Be Revamped </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 24 (Xinhua) -- China plans to reform its tens
of thousands of rural credit agencies and to turn them into
genuine cooperative banking institutions over the next two years.
</P>
<P>
This was revealed here today by Dai Xianglong, governor of the
People's Bank of China at the opening of a national work
conference on reforming the administrative system of the rural
banking sector.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is being held by the State Council
Inter-Departmental Group on Rural Banking Restructuring and is
expected to last for three days. Dai is also head of the group.
</P>
<P>
In his speech Dai said that to build rural credit agencies into
cooperative banking institutions is in line with the demands of
rural economic development and banking reform.
</P>
<P>
When rural credit agencies become cooperative banking
institutions they will be able to raise funds for the agricultural
sector effectively, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Dai announced that all the over 50,000 credit agencies
scattered across the country have been separated from control by
the Agricultural Bank of China and will operate independently
under the administration of over 2,000 county-based local
headquarters.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
