<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rabies Hits Somalia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Rabies has occurred in
war-torn Somalia as some victims either die immediately or suffer
mental sickness or barks like a dog, local doctors in capital
Mogadishu said here today.
</P>
<P>
Currently there is no medicine available in the Horn of
African country to treat the dog bites, let alone local vets to
take care of the dogs against catching such diseases, they
warned.
</P>
<P>
In Qoryolei, 80 km south of Mogadishu, a young boy died only
two days ago after a dog bit him. The dog died itself during the
struggle with the young boy.
</P>
<P>
In Afgoie district, 30 km south of Mogadishu, seven women were
bitten by dogs in separate cases. Two of them are at present in
critical condition suffering from hysteria and serious
lacerations on their heads caused by the bites of the dogs.
</P>
<P>
Hyenas, a dangerous animal which eats human fresh, also began
to be seen in the streets in Mogadishu, local residents said. But
so far there are no reports of people being attacked. Somalia is
hard hit by drought which has brought famine to parts of the
country.
</P>
<P>
More animals are believed to be hiding in the old wrecked
buildings in the center of Mogadishu, but nobody seems to know
how these animals, especially the hyenas and leopards, could
reach right there. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
