<HEADLINE> Tunisian President Meets French Defense Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TUNIS, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Tunisian President Zine El
Abidine Ben Ali today discussed with visiting French Defense
Minister Charles Millon ways to cooperate in maintaining peace and
security in the Mediterranean region and Africa.
</P>
<P>
Millon said that France and Tunisia will strengthen defense
cooperation in "operational and logistical fields" and increase
joint military training programs and exchange of military
information.
</P>
<P>
