<HEADLINE> Cyprus President Pays Tribute to Deng </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus President Glafcos
Clerides today visited the Chinese embassy here to pay his
tribute to Deng Xiaoping, who passed away in Beijing last
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
President Clerides signed his name on the condolence registry,
expressing his deep sorrow over the passing of the Chinese leader.
</P>
<P>
Over the past few days, Cyprus' parliament speaker, deputy
speaker, some government ministers, political party leaders and
friendly personalities from various circles as well as foreign
diplomatic envoys visited the Chinese embassy here to pay their
respects to late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
George Vassiliou, former President of Cyprus and Chairman of
the United Democrats Party, highly evaluated the role of Deng in
the documentary film "Deng Xiaoping."
</P>
<P>
The former president wrote the following words in the
condolence registry: "Comrade Deng was a great statesman and
leader of the Chinese people. He has greatly contributed to
fostering cooperation between the countries of the world and for
promoting peaceful cooperation among nations. The people of Cyprus
will always cherish his memory."
</P>
<P>
Representatives of the Chinese corporations in Cyprus and
overseas Chinese students also visited the Chinese embassy to
offer their condolences. 
