<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Leaders Meet US Secretary of State </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
and Premier Li Peng met here tonight with visiting US Secretary of
State Madeleine Albright.
</P>
<P>
Albright conveyed US President Bill Clinton's condolences over
the passing away of Deng Xiaoping. She also handed letters of
condolences from Clinton to Jiang and Zhuo Lin, Deng's widow.
</P>
<P>
Albright referred Deng as a respectable, great and historic
figure whose leadership has produced dramatic economic
transformation for China and who has contributed much to the
development of the Sino-US relations.
</P>
<P>
She offered her personal condolences over Deng's death.
</P>
<P>
Jiang and Li said Deng was an outstanding leader whose prestige
was recognized by the whole Party, the whole Army and the people
of all ethnic groups throughout China.
</P>
<P>
They said Deng made indelible contributions to the victory of
the New Democratic Revolution and the founding of New China, and
to the establishment, consolidation and growth of socialism in
China.
</P>
<P>
Deng also made contributions of historical importance to
creating a new scene for the country's independent diplomacy of
peace, to develop friendly ties of cooperation with other
countries, and to normalize and push forward the Sino-US relations.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders told Albright that the Chinese people will
cherish the memory of the late Deng's great historical
contributions, and will continue to take Deng's road.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, when recalling his meeting with President Clinton in
Manila last November, said the two heads of state have set the
principles for the continuous improvement and development of
bilateral ties, and that the two sides should make efforts to this
end.
</P>
<P>
China and the US are two countries of major importance in the
world, the Chinese president said, and they share broad common
interests.
</P>
<P>
He said great potentials are yet to be tapped between China and
the US, especially in developing mutually-benefitting trade and
economic cooperation, jointly maintaining global and regional
peace, promoting the growth and prosperity of the world
economy. And such potentialities are solid foundations for the
growth of bilateral ties, Jiang added.
</P>
<P>
Despite differences, Jiang said, the two countries should view
the bilateral ties from a more farsighted perspective. They should
increase understanding, seek common ground while reserving
differences and expand their cooperation to meet the fundamental
interests of the two peoples, and serve peace, stability and
prosperity of the Asia-Pacific region and of the world.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said it is a major task of the Chinese and American
leaders at the turning of the century to bring a healthy and
stable bilateral relationship of sustained development into the
21st century, based on the three Sino-US joint communiques.
</P>
<P>
This historical task, he stressed, requires the courage and
farsightedness as demonstrated by the leaders of the two countries
when they opened the relations between China and the US in the
1970's.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that to this end, he is willing to make concerted
efforts with his US counterpart.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
