<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkey for Direct Talks Between Rival Cypriots </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Turkey always supports the
direct talks between two communities of divided Cyprus, said
Turkish Deputy Prime Minister and Foreign Minister Tansu Ciller
here today.
</P>
<P>
Ciller told the visiting British Special Envoy on Cyprus issue
David Hanney, "We have been expecting the dialog to be held
between the two communities of Cyprus as soon as possible for a
long time."
</P>
<P>
It is very necessary for Hanney to mediate for the dialog
and peace process between Turkish and Greek Cypriots as soon
as possible, added the Turkish foreign minister.
</P>
<P>
On the Cypriot government's purchase of the Russian-made S-300
anti-aircraft missiles, Ciller said that it is "not helpful
to peace" in this region.
</P>
<P>
She stressed that northern Cyprus and Turkey would not
accept the deployment of the 150-kilometer-range missiles on the
east Mediterranean island of divided Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
For his part, Hanney said that the dialog should be
secured between the two communities of the island in a bid to
solve the Cyprus issue.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus remains divided since 1974 when Turkey occupied the
northern third of the strategic island in the wake of an
abortive coup by supporters of union with Greece.
</P>
<P>
At present, some 35,000 Turkish troops are stationed on the
island to protect the Turkish Cypriots. 
</P>
</TEXT>
