<HEADLINE> Lithuanian President Visits Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Lithuanian President Algirdas
Brazauskas began his two-day official visit to Greece today with
meetings with his Greek counterpart, Kostis Stephanopoulos, and
Prime Minister Costas Simitis.
</P>
<P>
The focus of discussions, Brazauskas said after his meeting
with Stephanopoulos, was NATO's expansion and Lithuania's
prospects of joining the European Union.
</P>
<P>
The Greek president said he was certain that Lithuania and all
the Baltic states were an "integral part of Europe" and had every
right to join European organizations.
</P>
<P>
Brazauskas said they had discussed NATO's expansion eastwards
and referred to Russia's positions and the role Moscow could play.
</P>
<P>
"Greece's experiences as a member of the EU and NATO are very
useful to Lithuania," he said. 
</P>
