<DOCNO> XIE19970225.0305 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France Hails Algeria's Decision to Resume Flight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, February 24 (Xinhua) -- France today hailed the decision
by Algeria to resume the direct flight of Air Algeria between
Algiers and Paris after a two-year suspension of the flight by
Algiers.
</P>
<P>
"We have been informed of the decision of the Algerian side to
resume its service to Paris by Air Algeria on the basis of
discussions between Algerian and French experts," said French
Foreign Ministry spokesman Jacques Rummelhardt.
</P>
<P>
Air Algeria, which served the only direct airline between
Algiers and Paris, suspended its flight to the French capital in
June 1995 after France asked it to remove its terminal from the
Orly-Sud Airport south of Paris to the Roissy Airport north of
Paris.
</P>
<P>
France cited security reasons and described Air Algeria as a
"high risk" target by Islamic extremists, while Algeria
considered the decision as "discriminatory."
</P>
<P>
"The French government always shows the hope that Air Algeria
could resume its activities from Paris as rapidly as possible,"
said the spokesman. "We cannot but rejoice over the decision
announced yesterday (by Algeria)."
</P>
<P>
He said that French experts are contacting Air Algeria on
practical arrangements to install the air company at a terminal in
the Roissy Airport.
</P>
<P>
"The preoccupation for an all-out security (for the air
company) is a constant preoccupation of the French authorities,"
he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
