<HEADLINE> Tatarstan President Visits Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Tatarstan President M. Shaimiyev
arrived here today for a three-day visit to Egypt, the Egyptian
Middle East News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak held a meeting earlier today
with the visiting president, which was also attended by Egyptian
Foreign Minister Amr Moussa and Deputy Prime Minister and Minister
of Agriculture and Land Reclamation Youssef Wali.
</P>
<P>
The talks focused on means of bolstering bilateral ties and
current international conditions, especially in Central Asia.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Egypt's Nimoufiya governorate, about 100
kilometers north of Cairo, and Khazan, the capital of Tatarstan,
an autonomous republic in the Russian Federation, signed a
twinship agreement.
</P>
<P>
Tatarstan, with a population of over 5 million, boasts a large
number of mosques and ancient Islamic buildings.
</P>
<P>
It is rich in oil and natural gas and has developed industries
in the field of aircraft and big trucks along with considerable
agricultural produce. 
</P>
