<HEADLINE> Deng's Contributions to Taiwan Affairs Recalled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese officials and scholars
connected with Taiwan affairs said that Deng Xiaoping's theory of
"one country, two systems" has made a great and indelible
contribution to the country's reunification cause.
</P>
<P>
Leading officials of the Central Committee of the Taiwan
Democratic Self-Government League, All-China Federation of Taiwan
Compatriots, Association for Relations Across the Taiwan Straits
and other organizations and institutions connected with Taiwan
affairs participated in a discussion here today to cherish the
memory of Deng, who died in Beijing last Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The discussion was presided over by Chen Yunlin, director of
the Taiwan Work Office of the Central Committee of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) and Taiwan Affairs Office of the State
Council.
</P>
<P>
As one of the top members of New China's first generation of
leaders and the core of the second generation of leadership, the
officials noted, Deng was many times engaged in making policies on
Taiwan affairs.
</P>
<P>
They pointed out that the reunification of China was one of the
three major tasks for the whole Party and the whole people, and
Deng initiated the theory of "one country, two systems" as a
practical solution to the Taiwan question.
</P>
<P>
Deng made great efforts to promote peaceful negotiations
between the CPC and Taiwan's Kuomintang, as well as to push
forward economic ties and non-official exchanges between both
sides of the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
Guided by Deng's theory, relations across the Taiwan Straits
have experienced historic changes in the past few years, the
discussion participants agreed.
</P>
<P>
They also expressed their intention to turn grief into strength
and to do an even better job of dealing with Taiwan affairs, by
sticking to the principle of "peaceful reunification within the
framework of one country, two systems".  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
