<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese People Recall Deng's Merits in Economic Reform (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Chinese people have received unprecedented benefits from
Deng Xiaoping's three-step strategy for economic development.
</P>
<P>
"Every household in our company has refrigerators and color TV
sets now. However, there were only four refrigerators and six
color TV sets among some 3,000 employees in 1980," said Wu Zukai,
a chief engineer with the Rainbow Group.
</P>
<P>
"My two sons have returned to work after studying in Britain
and the United States, because they are confident in the country's
future since Deng Xiaoping has blueprinted our future
development," Wu said.
</P>
<P>
Deng had urged Shanghai, China's largest city and economic
center, to take good advantage of favorable conditions to speed up
economic reconstruction.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with his proposal, Shanghai's industrial sector
plans to achieve an annual increasing rate of 14 percent in the
next four years, said Xu Zhiyi, director of the Shanghai Municipal
Economic Commission.
</P>
<P>
Guided by Deng's three-step strategy, local economy of Yan'an
City in northwest China's Shaanxi Province has entered a new era
step by step.
</P>
<P>
Yan'an, known as a sacred place of China's revolution, has seen
local residents' annual income rise to some 1,100 yuan, more than
ten times that of 1978.
</P>
<P>
"We will never forget Deng, because he always paid great
attention to the area's economic development," the locals said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970225.0318 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Switzerland Pledges Aid to Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, February 24 (Xinhua) -- The Swiss government
today pledged to allocate a total of 10 Billion Tanzania
Shillings (about 16.6 million U.S. Dollars) for various
development projects mostly in the health sector in Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
According to a statement issued by the Swiss embassy here,
this was said by Swiss Ambassador Lise Farve over the weekend at
a ceremony to mark the completion of the rehabilitation work of
the National Institute of Medical Research (NIMR) headquarters
here with Swiss aid.
</P>
<P>
She said the new financial assistance will cover the Dar es
Salaam Urban Health Project, the National Tuberculosis and
Leprosy Program, the St. Francis designated district hospital in
Kilombero district, Ifakara Research Center, as well as the
National Institute for Medical Research, for the next two years.
</P>
<P>
A big part of these projects were concentrated along the Great
Uhuru Corridor which (TAZARA) transverses four regions including
Dar es Salaam, Morogoro, Coast and Tanga, the Swiss ambassador
added.
</P>
<P>
Switzerland is one of the main donors for rehabilitation and
development projects in Tanzania. Its support currently has been
focusing on infrastructure, income generation, rural development
and health sectors in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
