<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese People Recalls Deng's Merits in Economic Reform (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 24 (Xinhua) -- For the past several days,
people across the country have vowed to adhere to Deng Xiaoping's
theory of building socialism with Chinese characteristics under
the Communist Party's leadership with Jiang Zemin at the core.
</P>
<P>
Deng passed away last Wednesday at the age of 93.
</P>
<P>
Recalling the outstanding deeds of Deng Xiaoping, the people
said they had heartfelt feelings that there would not have been
earth-shaking changes in China without the basic principle of
taking economic development as the central task and persisting in
the Party's leadership and socialism.
</P>
<P>
"Facts have proven that the principle has brought about
benefits to the people and the country, and it is the only way to
build the country's prosperity and increase the people's
wellbeing," said Yang Chungui, vice-president of the Party School
of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC).
</P>
<P>
This principle should remain unchanged for a long time to come,
just as what Deng Xiaoping had stressed time and again, Yang said.
</P>
<P>
Villagers who have become beneficiaries of Deng Xiaoping's
economic reform program remember Deng as a great reformer who
helped them get rich. They are able to build new brick houses and
buy household electrical appliances.
</P>
<P>
The mountainous village of Dazhai in Shanxi Province used to be
a national model designated by late Chairman Mao Zedong to exhibit
the spirit of socialism. However, the villagers lived poor lives
in those days.
</P>
<P>
Now annual per capita income of local farmers has reached 2,100
yuan (253 US dollars), 11 times that of 1980 when Deng Xiaoping
just began his economic reform program.
</P>
<P>
"Reform and opening-up bring about earth-shaking changes in
Dazhai," Guo Fenglian, secretary of the village's Communist Party
Committee, said with emotion.
</P>
<P>
Similarly, many factories were in great chaos under the
"Leftist" policy of class struggle during the "Cultural
Revolution" (1966-1977). With great care of Deng Xiaoping, the
enterprises restored normal production, according to Liu Benren,
general manager of the Wuhan Iron and Steel Company.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
