<DOCNO> XIE19970225.0320 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese People Recall Deng's Merits in Economic Reform (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Deng Xiaoping set three criteria to assess the work in all
fields, namely whether it helps develop productive forces, enhance
China's comprehensive strength, and improve people's living
standards.
</P>
<P>
Leading officials and ordinary people agreed that the three
criteria greatly liberated people's mind and further pushed
forward China's modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
Wang Zhongyu, minister in charge of the State Economic and
Trade Commission, said that Deng was a pioneer in reforming
state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Ma Jinlong, deputy-director of the Wenzhou City Commission for
Restructing the Economy, attributed the city's rapid economic
growth to its adoption of Deng's three criteria. All major
economic indicators scored an annual increase rate of over 30
percent from 1992 to 1996.
</P>
<P>
Fenggang township in Dongguan City, Guangdong Province, took
the lead in taking in foreign investment and developing collective
economy. Deng Yaohui, secretary of the local Communist Party
branch, said excitedly that they owe all their success to Comrade
Deng Xiaoping's theory.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Weirong, manager of a food and drink store in Hangzhou,
capital city of Zhejiang Province, expressed his wish to help more
people get rich in accordance with the teachings of Comrade Deng
Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
Yu Zhen, chairman of the Council of Light Industry, emphasized
that the Chinese people should rally around the CPC Central
Committee with Comrade Jiang Zemin at the core to develop the
country in line with the teaching of Comrade Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
</TEXT>
