<HEADLINE> Arab League Warns Against Israeli Settlements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, February 24 (Xinhua) -- The Arab League General
Secretariat warned today that the continuation of building Israeli
settlements in the occupied Arab lands will have their grave
impact on the peace process.
</P>
<P>
The General Secretariat, in a statement, said the erection of
settlements in Jerusalem and the Golan Heights constitute
"flagrant violation" of international legitimacy and run against
all United Nations resolutions.
</P>
<P>
Saying that these settlements will reflect negatively on the
peace process, the statement urged the UN Security Council and the
co-sponsors of the peace process, notably the United States, to
move quickly to force Israel to stop this settlement policy.
</P>
<P>
The General Secretariat is holding contacts with the Arab
League delegation to the UN in coordination with the Organization
of Islamic Conference and the Non-aligned Movement to follow up
this issue and refer it to the Security Council, said the
statement.
</P>
<P>
The secretariat followed up with concern over the past few days
the building of a new settlement in southeast Jerusalem in Abu
Guneim Mount(known as Har Homa to Israelis), it said.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Prime Minister Binyamin Netanyahu said last Friday that
in spite of fierce Palestinian opposition he will submit to his
Cabinet a plan for the construction of a Jewish neighborhood in
disputed east Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The Har Homa project of 6,500 housing units is expected to win
overwhelming approval of Cabinet ministers, according to the
Israel Radio.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinians are seek to make east Jerusalem, captured by
Israel in the 1967 Mideast war, the capital of their future
state. 
</P>
</TEXT>
