this morning in southern Algeria, killing one person and wounding
13 others, the Algerian Security Department announced.
</P>
<P>
In a statement released following the blast, the department
said the explosion took place at a wholesale market in Bufarik in
Bleida province, some 50 kilometers south of the capital city of
Algiers.
</P>
<P>
Officers of the Civil Defense and Security Departments rushed
to the scene of the explosion, and the victims of the blast were
rushed to hospital to receive first-aid treatment.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, an official of the Algerian Security Department
disclosed that tension in Algeria has eased in comparison with the
period during the Muslim fasting month of Ramadan.
</P>
<P>
He attributed the relaxation to the Algerian government's
action in reinforcing the Algerian Armed and Security forces
responsible for combating terrorism throughout the country.
</P>
<P>
The official, whose name was withheld, added that action is
being taken along with the ongoing consultations between the
government and opposition parties to combat terrorism and create a
democratic atmosphere in Algeria.
</P>
<P>
The official said that Algeria is capable of stamping out
terrorist acts in a span of two years. 
