<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hussein Attends Memorial Ceremony of Deng Xiaoping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, February 24 (Xinhua) -- King Hussein of Jordan attended
tonight the memorial ceremony of Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping held
in the Chinese Embassy here.
</P>
<P>
"I deeply admire Deng," Hussein said at the memorial ceremony.
</P>
<P>
"I express my deep condolences and sincere sympathy to the
death of Deng Xiaoping, our respectable and great friend and
leader of the Chinese people, as well as to the Chinese people and
leaders on behalf of myself, the Hashimite family and the
Jordanian people," wrote the king on the condolence book.
</P>
<P>
"In the long years, Deng and I made deep friendship, which
will last forever between Jordan and China as well as the Jordanian
people and the Chinese people," Hussein wrote while Crown prince
Hassan and other Jordanian government's officials standing beside.
</P>
<P>
After the death of Deng, the king had sent a cable of
condolence to Chinese President Jiang Zemin, expressing his regret
for the loss of one of the world's leading intellectuals.
</P>
<P>
He recalled Deng's contribution to the prosperity of the
Chinese people and the great role he played in international
politics.
</P>
<P>
Also attending the memorial ceremony tonight are Jordanian
senior politicians and several ministers. About 200 people
attended the ceremony here. 
</P>
</TEXT>
