<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU Mourns Death of Deng Xiaoping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, February 24 (Xinhua) -- The European Union today
expressed its condolences on the death of China's leader Deng
Xiaoping, saying that his death will undoubtedly be a great loss
to China and its people.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued here Monday, the EU said that Deng had
stimulated economic development in China, raised the standard of
living and prosperity of the Chinese population and played a large
role in the opening up of China to the international community.
</P>
<P>
He would be regarded by future generations as an historic
figure, the statement said, though Deng did not hold any political
office during the last years of his life. 
</P>
</TEXT>
