<HEADLINE> UAE Calls on PA Not to Compromise with Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, February 24 (Xinhua) -- The United Arab Emirates
(UAE) today called on the Palestine Authority (PA) to insist on
legal rights of the Palestinian people and not to compromise in
the Israeli-Palestinian peace talks, UAE's news agency WAM
reported.
</P>
<P>
UAE Defense Minister and Dubai Crown Prince Sheikh Muhammad bin
Rashid al-Maktoum called on the PA and Palestinian negotiators
for the Israeli-Palestine peace talks not to compromise and give
up legal rights of the Palestinian people, no matter what the
pressure is, WAM said.
</P>
<P>
The defense minister made the remarks in Dubai during his
meeting with Mahmoud Abbas (Abu Mazen), member of the Palestine
Liberation Organization's Executive Committee, who is currently
visiting the UAE.
</P>
<P>
The minister also stressed UAE's support to the Palestinian
people, saying that the UAE government and people will continue their
support for the Palestinian people until they can enjoy freedom
and independence.
</P>
<P>
Abu Mazen began his visit to the UAE from Friday to seek the
UAE's political and financial support for the PA, and to discuss
with UAE officials the current Arab developments.
</P>
<P>
It was not known for the time being whether the UAE government
has promised to provide financial support to the Palestinians, but
some diplomats here said the UAE has financed settlement projects
for the Palestinians in Jerusalem and Gaza Strip before.
</P>
<P>
Abu Mazen's visit to the UAE comes after Israel's right-wing
Prime Minister Binyamin Netanyahu last week announced the
construction of a new Jewish neighborhood in the undeveloped Har
Homa area on the southern edge of East Jerusalem. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
