<DATE_TIME> 1997-02-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU President Calls for New Vision of EU-US Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, February 24 (Xinhua) -- President of the European
Union (EU) Jacques Santer recently called for a new shared vision
for the future of the relationship between the EU and the United
States, it was learned here today.
</P>
<P>
The transatlantic relations do not mean anything if they are
not "sustained by a strong determination to build a real EU-U.S.
partnership," Santer said in a speech made in Brussels on February
21.
</P>
<P>
He said that any long-term vision of Euro-American relations
must recognize that the present concentration of power and
influence was being gradually diluted.
</P>
<P>
The EU chief called for a new shared vision for the future,
saying that the U.S. should be ready to "share influence and power
more equally with its European partners" and to understand the
"specificity of this unique animal which we call the European
Union."
</P>
<P>
He explained that there was no point in criticizing the EU for
not behaving as if it were a single nation state, adding that the
EU needed the cooperation of various emerging international forces
to address global and regional issues.
</P>
<P>
Santer said that the EU and the U.S. must help solve the
difficulties that the United Nations face. "UN bashing might be
fashionable until we discover that we are shooting ourselves in
the foot," he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
